[0.001, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[46;1H\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f2,0-1\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.275, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\r\u001b[A\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Enable the PHP scripting language engine under Apache.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/engine\u001b[K\r\nengine =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive determines whether or not PHP will recognize code between\u001b[K\r\n; <? and ?> tags as PHP source which should be processed as such. It is\u001b[K\r\n; generally recommended that <?php and ?> should be used and that this feature\u001b[K\r\n; should be disabled, as enabling it may result in issues when generating XML\u001b[K\r\n; documents, however this remains supported for backward compatibility reasons.\u001b[K\r\n; Note that this directive does not control the <?= shorthand tag, which can be\u001b[K\r\n; used regardless of this directive.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/short-open-tag\u001b[K\r\nshort_open_tag =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The number of significant digits displayed in floating point numbers.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/precision\u001b[K\r\nprecision = 14\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Output buffering is a mechanism for controlling how much output data\u001b[K\r\n; (excluding headers and cookies) PHP should keep internally before pushing that\u001b[K\r\n; data to the client. If your application's output exceeds this setting, PHP\u001b[K\r\n; will send that data in chunks of roughly the size you specify.\u001b[K\r\n; Turning on this setting and managing its maximum buffer size can yield some\u001b[K\r\n; interesting side-effects depending on your application and web server.\u001b[K\r\n; You may be able to send headers and cookies after you've already sent output\u001b[K\r\n; through print or echo. You also may see performance benefits if your server is\u001b[K\r\n; emitting less packets due to buffered output versus PHP streaming the output\u001b[K\r\n; as it gets it. On production servers, 4096 bytes is a good setting for performance\u001b[K\r\n; reasons.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: Output buffering can also be controlled via Output Buffering Control\u001b[K\r\n;   functions.\u001b[K\r\n; Possible Values:\u001b[K\r\n;   On = Enabled and buffer is unlimited. (Use with caution)\u001b[K\r\n;   Off = Disabled\u001b[K\r\n;   Integer = Enables the buffer and sets its maximum size in bytes.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: This directive is hardcoded to Off for the CLI SAPI\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: 4096\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: 4096\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/output-buffering\u001b[K\r\noutput_buffering = 4096\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f1,20          9\u001b[1;20H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.632, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;20H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\n; You can redirect all of the output of your scripts to a function.  For\u001b[K\r\n; example, if you set output_handler to \"mb_output_handler\", character\u001b[K\r\n; encoding will be transparently converted to the specified encoding.\u001b[K\r\n; Setting any output handler automatically turns on output buffering.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: People who wrote portable scripts should not depend on this ini\u001b[K\r\n;   directive. Instead, explicitly set the output handler using ob_start().\u001b[K\r\n;   Using this ini directive may cause problems unless you know what script\u001b[K\r\n;   is doing.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: You cannot use both \"mb_output_handler\" with \"ob_iconv_handler\"\u001b[K\r\n;   and you cannot use both \"ob_gzhandler\" and \"zlib.output_compression\".\u001b[K\r\n; Note: output_handler must be empty if this is set 'On' !!!!\u001b[K\r\n;   Instead you must use zlib.output_handler.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/output-handler\u001b[K\r\n;output_handler =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; URL rewriter function rewrites URL on the fly by using\u001b[K\r\n; output buffer. You can set target tags by this configuration.\u001b[K\r\n; \"form\" tag is special tag. It will add hidden input tag to pass values.\u001b[K\r\n; Refer to session.trans_sid_tags for usage.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"form=\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"form=\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"form=\"\u001b[K\r\n;url_rewriter.tags\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; URL rewriter will not rewrite absolute URL nor form by default. To enable\u001b[K\r\n; absolute URL rewrite, allowed hosts must be defined at RUNTIME.\u001b[K\r\n; Refer to session.trans_sid_hosts for more details.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"\"\u001b[K\r\n;url_rewriter.hosts\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Transparent output compression using the zlib library\u001b[K\r\n; Valid values for this option are 'off', 'on', or a specific buffer size\u001b[K\r\n; to be used for compression (default is 4KB)\u001b[K\r\n; Note: Resulting chunk size may vary due to nature of compression. PHP\u001b[K\r\n;   outputs chunks that are few hundreds bytes each as a result of\u001b[K\r\n;   compression. If you prefer a larger chunk size for better\u001b[K\r\n;   performance, enable output_buffering in addition.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: You need to use zlib.output_handler instead of the standard\u001b[K\r\n;   output_handler, or otherwise the output will be corrupted.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/zlib.output-compression\u001b[K\r\nzlib.output_compression =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f225,23         12\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.344, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/zlib.output-compression-level\u001b[K\r\n;zlib.output_compression_level = -1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; You cannot specify additional output handlers if zlib.output_compression\u001b[K\r\n; is activated here. This setting does the same as output_handler but in\u001b[K\r\n; a different order.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/zlib.output-handler\u001b[K\r\n;zlib.output_handler =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Implicit flush tells PHP to tell the output layer to flush itself\u001b[K\r\n; automatically after every output block.  This is equivalent to calling the\u001b[K\r\n; PHP function flush() after each and every call to print() or echo() and each\u001b[K\r\n; and every HTML block.  Turning this option on has serious performance\u001b[K\r\n; implications and is generally recommended for debugging purposes only.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/implicit-flush\u001b[K\r\n; Note: This directive is hardcoded to On for the CLI SAPI\u001b[K\r\nimplicit_flush =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The unserialize callback function will be called (with the undefined class'\u001b[K\r\n; name as parameter), if the unserializer finds an undefined class\u001b[K\r\n; which should be instantiated. A warning appears if the specified function is\u001b[K\r\n; not defined, or if the function doesn't include/implement the missing class.\u001b[K\r\n; So only set this entry, if you really want to implement such a\u001b[K\r\n; callback-function.\u001b[K\r\nunserialize_callback_func =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The unserialize_max_depth specifies the default depth limit for unserialized\u001b[K\r\n; structures. Setting the depth limit too high may result in stack overflows\u001b[K\r\n; during unserialization. The unserialize_max_depth ini setting can be\u001b[K\r\n; overridden by the max_depth option on individual unserialize() calls.\u001b[K\r\n; A value of 0 disables the depth limit.\u001b[K\r\n;unserialize_max_depth = 4096\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; When floats & doubles are serialized, store serialize_precision significant\u001b[K\r\n; digits after the floating point. The default value ensures that when floats\u001b[K\r\n; are decoded with unserialize, the data will remain the same.\u001b[K\r\n; The value is also used for json_encode when encoding double values.\u001b[K\r\n; If -1 is used, then dtoa mode 0 is used which automatically select the best\u001b[K\r\n; precision.\u001b[K\r\nserialize_precision =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; open_basedir, if set, limits all file operations to the defined directory\u001b[K\r\n; and below.  This directive makes most sense if used in a per-directory\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f69,23         14\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.283, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; or per-virtualhost web server configuration file.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: disables the realpath cache\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/open-basedir\u001b[K\r\n;open_basedir =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive allows you to disable certain functions.\u001b[K\r\n; It receives a comma-delimited list of function names.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/disable-functions\u001b[K\r\ndisable_functions =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Colors for Syntax Highlighting mode.  Anything that's acceptable in\u001b[K\r\n; <span style=\"color: ???????\"> would work.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/syntax-highlighting\u001b[K\r\n;highlight.string  = #DD0000\u001b[K\r\n;highlight.comment = #FF9900\u001b[K\r\n;highlight.keyword = #007700\u001b[K\r\n;highlight.default = #0000BB\u001b[K\r\n;highlight.html    = #000000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If enabled, the request will be allowed to complete even if the user aborts\u001b[K\r\n; the request. Consider enabling it if executing long requests, which may end up\u001b[K\r\n; being interrupted by the user or a browser timing out. PHP's default behavior\u001b[K\r\n; is to disable this feature.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/ignore-user-abort\u001b[K\r\n;ignore_user_abort = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Determines the size of the realpath cache to be used by PHP. This value should\u001b[K\r\n; be increased on systems where PHP opens many files to reflect the quantity of\u001b[K\r\n; the file operations performed.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: if open_basedir is set, the cache is disabled\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/realpath-cache-size\u001b[K\r\n;realpath_cache_size = 4096k\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Duration of time, in seconds for which to cache realpath information for a given\u001b[K\r\n; file or directory. For systems with rarely changing files, consider increasing this\u001b[K\r\n; value.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/realpath-cache-ttl\u001b[K\r\n;realpath_cache_ttl = 120\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables or disables the circular reference collector.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/zend.enable-gc\u001b[K\r\nzend.enable_gc =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If enabled, scripts may be written in encodings that are incompatible with\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f313,23         17\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.226, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; the scanner.  CP936, Big5, CP949 and Shift_JIS are the examples of such\u001b[K\r\n; encodings.  To use this feature, mbstring extension must be enabled.\u001b[K\r\n;zend.multibyte = Off\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allows to set the default encoding for the scripts.  This value will be used\u001b[K\r\n; unless \"declare(encoding=...)\" directive appears at the top of the script.\u001b[K\r\n; Only affects if zend.multibyte is set.\u001b[K\r\n;zend.script_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allows to include or exclude arguments from stack traces generated for exceptions.\u001b[K\r\n; In production, it is recommended to turn this setting on to prohibit the output\u001b[K\r\n; of sensitive information in stack traces\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: On\u001b[K\r\nzend.exception_ignore_args =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allows setting the maximum string length in an argument of a stringified stack trace\u001b[K\r\n; to a value between 0 and 1000000.\u001b[K\r\n; This has no effect when zend.exception_ignore_args is enabled.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: 15\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: 15\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: 0\u001b[K\r\n; In production, it is recommended to set this to 0 to reduce the output\u001b[K\r\n; of sensitive information in stack traces.\u001b[K\r\nzend.exception_string_param_max_len = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Miscellaneous ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Decides whether PHP may expose the fact that it is installed on the server\u001b[K\r\n; (e.g. by adding its signature to the Web server header).  It is no security\u001b[K\r\n; threat in any way, but it makes it possible to determine whether you use PHP\u001b[K\r\n; on your server or not.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/expose-php\u001b[K\r\nexpose_php =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Resource Limits ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum execution time of each script, in seconds\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/max-execution-time\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f57,0-1        19\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.280, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Note: This directive is hardcoded to 0 for the CLI SAPI\u001b[K\r\nmax_execution_time = 30\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum amount of time each script may spend parsing request data. It's a good\u001b[K\r\n; idea to limit this time on productions servers in order to eliminate unexpectedly\u001b[K\r\n; long running scripts.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: This directive is hardcoded to -1 for the CLI SAPI\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: -1 (Unlimited)\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: 60 (60 seconds)\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: 60 (60 seconds)\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/max-input-time\u001b[K\r\nmax_input_time = 60\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum input variable nesting level\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/max-input-nesting-level\u001b[K\r\n;max_input_nesting_level = 64\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; How many GET/POST/COOKIE input variables may be accepted\u001b[K\r\n;max_input_vars = 1000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; How many multipart body parts (combined input variable and file uploads) may\u001b[K\r\n; be accepted.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: -1 (Sum of max_input_vars and max_file_uploads)\u001b[K\r\n;max_multipart_body_parts = 1500\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum amount of memory a script may consume\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/memory-limit\u001b[K\r\nmemory_limit =\u001b[92m 128M\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\nmax_memory_limit =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Error handling and logging ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive informs PHP of which errors, warnings and notices you would like\u001b[K\r\n; it to take action for. The recommended way of setting values for this\u001b[K\r\n; directive is through the use of the error level constants and bitwise\u001b[K\r\n; operators. The error level constants are below here for convenience as well as\u001b[K\r\n; some common settings and their meanings.\u001b[K\r\n; By default, PHP is set to take action on all errors, notices and warnings EXCEPT\u001b[K\r\n; those related to E_NOTICE, which together cover best practices and\u001b[K\r\n; recommended coding standards in PHP. For performance reasons, this is the\u001b[K\r\n; recommend error reporting setting. Your production server shouldn't be wasting\u001b[K\r\n; resources complaining about best practices and coding standards. That's what\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f401,23         21\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.089, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; development servers and development settings are for.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: The php.ini-development file has this setting as E_ALL. This\u001b[K\r\n; means it pretty much reports everything which is exactly what you want during\u001b[K\r\n; development and early testing.\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; Error Level Constants:\u001b[K\r\n; E_ALL             - All errors and warnings\u001b[K\r\n; E_ERROR           - fatal run-time errors\u001b[K\r\n; E_RECOVERABLE_ERROR  - almost fatal run-time errors\u001b[K\r\n; E_WARNING         - run-time warnings (non-fatal errors)\u001b[K\r\n; E_PARSE           - compile-time parse errors\u001b[K\r\n; E_NOTICE          - run-time notices (these are warnings which often result\u001b[K\r\n;                     from a bug in your code, but it's possible that it was\u001b[K\r\n;                     intentional (e.g., using an uninitialized variable and\u001b[K\r\n;                     relying on the fact it is automatically initialized to an\u001b[K\r\n;                     empty string)\u001b[K\r\n; E_CORE_ERROR      - fatal errors that occur during PHP's initial startup\u001b[K\r\n; E_CORE_WARNING    - warnings (non-fatal errors) that occur during PHP's\u001b[K\r\n;                     initial startup\u001b[K\r\n; E_COMPILE_ERROR   - fatal compile-time errors\u001b[K\r\n; E_COMPILE_WARNING - compile-time warnings (non-fatal errors)\u001b[K\r\n; E_USER_ERROR      - user-generated error message\u001b[K\r\n; E_USER_WARNING    - user-generated warning message\u001b[K\r\n; E_USER_NOTICE     - user-generated notice message\u001b[K\r\n; E_DEPRECATED      - warn about code that will not work in future versions\u001b[K\r\n;                     of PHP\u001b[K\r\n; E_USER_DEPRECATED - user-generated deprecation warnings\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; Common Values:\u001b[K\r\n;   E_ALL (Show all errors, warnings and notices including coding standards.)\u001b[K\r\n;   E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE  (Show all errors, except for notices)\u001b[K\r\n;   E_COMPILE_ERROR|E_RECOVERABLE_ERROR|E_ERROR|E_CORE_ERROR  (Show only errors)\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: E_ALL\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: E_ALL\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: E_ALL & ~E_DEPRECATED\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/error-reporting\u001b[K\r\nerror_reporting =\u001b[92m E_ALL & ~E_DEPRECATED\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive controls whether or not and where PHP will output errors,\u001b[K\r\n; notices and warnings too. Error output is very useful during development, but\u001b[K\r\n; it could be very dangerous in production environments. Depending on the code\u001b[K\r\n; which is triggering the error, sensitive information could potentially leak\u001b[K\r\n; out of your application such as database usernames and passwords or worse.\u001b[K\r\n; For production environments, we recommend logging errors rather than\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f45,23         24\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.255, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; sending them to STDOUT.\u001b[K\r\n; Possible Values:\u001b[K\r\n;   Off = Do not display any errors\u001b[K\r\n;   stderr = Display errors to STDERR (affects only CGI/CLI binaries!)\u001b[K\r\n;   On or stdout = Display errors to STDOUT\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/display-errors\u001b[K\r\ndisplay_errors =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The display of errors which occur during PHP's startup sequence are handled\u001b[K\r\n; separately from display_errors. We strongly recommend you set this to 'off'\u001b[K\r\n; for production servers to avoid leaking configuration details.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/display-startup-errors\u001b[K\r\ndisplay_startup_errors =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Besides displaying errors, PHP can also log errors to locations such as a\u001b[K\r\n; server-specific log, STDERR, or a location specified by the error_log\u001b[K\r\n; directive found below. While errors should not be displayed on productions\u001b[K\r\n; servers they should still be monitored and logging is a great way to do that.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/log-errors\u001b[K\r\nlog_errors =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Do not log repeated messages. Repeated errors must occur in same file on same\u001b[K\r\n; line unless ignore_repeated_source is set true.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/ignore-repeated-errors\u001b[K\r\nignore_repeated_errors =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Ignore source of message when ignoring repeated messages. When this setting\u001b[K\r\n; is On you will not log errors with repeated messages from different files or\u001b[K\r\n; source lines.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/ignore-repeated-source\u001b[K\r\nignore_repeated_source =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This setting is off by default.\u001b[K\r\n;report_zend_debug = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f89,23         26\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.301, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Turn off normal error reporting and emit XML-RPC error XML\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/xmlrpc-errors\u001b[K\r\n;xmlrpc_errors = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; An XML-RPC faultCode\u001b[K\r\n;xmlrpc_error_number = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; When PHP displays or logs an error, it has the capability of formatting the\u001b[K\r\n; error message as HTML for easier reading. This directive controls whether\u001b[K\r\n; the error message is formatted as HTML or not.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: This directive is hardcoded to Off for the CLI SAPI\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/html-errors\u001b[K\r\n;html_errors = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If html_errors is set to On *and* docref_root is not empty, then PHP\u001b[K\r\n; produces clickable error messages that direct to a page describing the error\u001b[K\r\n; or function causing the error in detail.\u001b[K\r\n; You can download a copy of the PHP manual from https://php.net/docs\u001b[K\r\n; and change docref_root to the base URL of your local copy including the\u001b[K\r\n; leading '/'. You must also specify the file extension being used including\u001b[K\r\n; the dot. PHP's default behavior is to leave these settings empty, in which\u001b[K\r\n; case no links to documentation are generated.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: Never use this feature for production boxes.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/docref-root\u001b[K\r\n; Examples\u001b[K\r\n;docref_root = \"/phpmanual/\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/docref-ext\u001b[K\r\n;docref_ext = .html\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; String to output before an error message. PHP's default behavior is to leave\u001b[K\r\n; this setting blank.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/error-prepend-string\u001b[K\r\n; Example:\u001b[K\r\n;error_prepend_string = \"<span style='color: #ff0000'>\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; String to output after an error message. PHP's default behavior is to leave\u001b[K\r\n; this setting blank.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/error-append-string\u001b[K\r\n; Example:\u001b[K\r\n;error_append_string = \"</span>\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Log errors to specified file. PHP's default behavior is to leave this value\u001b[K\r\n; empty.\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f533,22         29\u001b[1;22H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.207, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;22H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; https://php.net/error-log\u001b[K\r\n; Example:\u001b[K\r\n;error_log = php_errors.log\u001b[K\r\n; Log errors to syslog (Event Log on Windows).\u001b[K\r\n;error_log = syslog\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The syslog ident is a string which is prepended to every message logged\u001b[K\r\n; to syslog. Only used when error_log is set to syslog.\u001b[K\r\n;syslog.ident = php\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The syslog facility is used to specify what type of program is logging\u001b[K\r\n; the message. Only used when error_log is set to syslog.\u001b[K\r\n;syslog.facility = user\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Set this to disable filtering control characters (the default).\u001b[K\r\n; Some loggers only accept NVT-ASCII, others accept anything that's not\u001b[K\r\n; control characters. If your logger accepts everything, then no filtering\u001b[K\r\n; is needed at all.\u001b[K\r\n; Allowed values are:\u001b[K\r\n;   ascii (all printable ASCII characters and NL)\u001b[K\r\n;   no-ctrl (all characters except control characters)\u001b[K\r\n;   all (all characters)\u001b[K\r\n;   raw (like \"all\", but messages are not split at newlines)\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/syslog.filter\u001b[K\r\n;syslog.filter = ascii\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;windows.show_crt_warning\u001b[K\r\n; Default value: 0\u001b[K\r\n; Development value: 0\u001b[K\r\n; Production value: 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive controls whether PHP will output the backtrace of fatal errors.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: On\u001b[K\r\n;fatal_error_backtraces = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Data Handling ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The separator used in PHP generated URLs to separate arguments.\u001b[K\r\n; PHP's default setting is \"&\".\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/arg-separator.output\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f77,23         31\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.241, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Example:\u001b[K\r\n;arg_separator.output = \"&amp;\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; List of separator(s) used by PHP to parse input URLs into variables.\u001b[K\r\n; PHP's default setting is \"&\".\u001b[K\r\n; NOTE: Every character in this directive is considered as separator!\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/arg-separator.input\u001b[K\r\n; Example:\u001b[K\r\n;arg_separator.input = \";&\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive determines which super global arrays are registered when PHP\u001b[K\r\n; starts up. G,P,C,E & S are abbreviations for the following respective super\u001b[K\r\n; globals: GET, POST, COOKIE, ENV and SERVER. There is a performance penalty\u001b[K\r\n; paid for the registration of these arrays and because ENV is not as commonly\u001b[K\r\n; used as the others, ENV is not recommended on productions servers. You\u001b[K\r\n; can still get access to the environment variables through getenv() should you\u001b[K\r\n; need to.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"EGPCS\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"GPCS\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"GPCS\";\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/variables-order\u001b[K\r\nvariables_order =\u001b[92m \"GPCS\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive determines which super global data (G,P & C) should be\u001b[K\r\n; registered into the super global array REQUEST. If so, it also determines\u001b[K\r\n; the order in which that data is registered. The values for this directive\u001b[K\r\n; are specified in the same manner as the variables_order directive,\u001b[K\r\n; EXCEPT one. Leaving this value empty will cause PHP to use the value set\u001b[K\r\n; in the variables_order directive. It does not mean it will leave the super\u001b[K\r\n; globals array REQUEST empty.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: None\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"GP\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"GP\"\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/request-order\u001b[K\r\nrequest_order =\u001b[92m \"GP\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive determines whether PHP registers $argv & $argc each time it\u001b[K\r\n; runs. $argv contains an array of all the arguments passed to PHP when a script\u001b[K\r\n; is invoked. $argc contains an integer representing the number of arguments\u001b[K\r\n; that were passed when the script was invoked. These arrays are extremely\u001b[K\r\n; useful when running scripts from the command line. When this directive is\u001b[K\r\n; enabled, registering these variables consumes CPU cycles and memory each time\u001b[K\r\n; a script is executed. For security reasons, this feature should be disabled\u001b[K\r\n; for non-CLI SAPIs.\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f621,23         33\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.209, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Note: This directive is ignored for the CLI SAPI\u001b[K\r\n; This directive is deprecated.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/register-argc-argv\u001b[K\r\n;register_argc_argv = Off\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; When enabled, the ENV, REQUEST and SERVER variables are created when they're\u001b[K\r\n; first used (Just In Time) instead of when the script starts. If these\u001b[K\r\n; variables are not used within a script, having this directive on will result\u001b[K\r\n; in a performance gain. The PHP directive register_argc_argv must be disabled\u001b[K\r\n; for this directive to have any effect.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/auto-globals-jit\u001b[K\r\nauto_globals_jit =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether PHP will read the POST data.\u001b[K\r\n; This option is enabled by default.\u001b[K\r\n; Most likely, you won't want to disable this option globally. It causes $_POST\u001b[K\r\n; and $_FILES to always be empty; the only way you will be able to read the\u001b[K\r\n; POST data will be through the php://input stream wrapper. This can be useful\u001b[K\r\n; to proxy requests or to process the POST data in a memory efficient fashion.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/enable-post-data-reading\u001b[K\r\n;enable_post_data_reading = Off\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum size of POST data that PHP will accept.\u001b[K\r\n; Its value may be 0 to disable the limit. It is ignored if POST data reading\u001b[K\r\n; is disabled through enable_post_data_reading.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/post-max-size\u001b[K\r\npost_max_size =\u001b[92m 8M\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Automatically add files before PHP document.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/auto-prepend-file\u001b[K\r\nauto_prepend_file =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Automatically add files after PHP document.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/auto-append-file\u001b[K\r\nauto_append_file =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; By default, PHP will output a media type using the Content-Type header. To\u001b[K\r\n; disable this, simply set it to be empty.\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; PHP's built-in default media type is set to text/html.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/default-mimetype\u001b[K\r\ndefault_mimetype =\u001b[92m \"text/html\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; PHP's default character set is set to UTF-8.\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f65,23         36\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.249, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; https://php.net/default-charset\u001b[K\r\ndefault_charset =\u001b[92m \"UTF-8\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; PHP internal character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/internal-encoding\u001b[K\r\n;internal_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; PHP input character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/input-encoding\u001b[K\r\n;input_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; PHP output character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[K\r\n; See also output_buffer.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/output-encoding\u001b[K\r\n;output_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Paths and Directories ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; UNIX: \"/path1:/path2\"\u001b[K\r\n;include_path = \".:/php/includes\"\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; Windows: \"\\path1;\\path2\"\u001b[K\r\n;include_path = \".;c:\\php\\includes\"\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; PHP's default setting for include_path is \".;/path/to/php/pear\"\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/include-path\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The root of the PHP pages, used only if nonempty.\u001b[K\r\n; if PHP was not compiled with FORCE_REDIRECT, you SHOULD set doc_root\u001b[K\r\n; if you are running php as a CGI under any web server (other than IIS)\u001b[K\r\n; see documentation for security issues.  The alternate is to use the\u001b[K\r\n; cgi.force_redirect configuration below\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/doc-root\u001b[K\r\ndoc_root =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The directory under which PHP opens the script using /~username used only\u001b[K\r\n; if nonempty.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/user-dir\u001b[K\r\nuser_dir =\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f709,0-1        38\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.216, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\n; Directory in which the loadable extensions (modules) reside.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/extension-dir\u001b[K\r\nextension_dir =\u001b[92m \"/usr/lib/php/modules/\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; On windows:\u001b[K\r\n;extension_dir = \"ext\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Directory where the temporary files should be placed.\u001b[K\r\n; Defaults to the system default (see sys_get_temp_dir)\u001b[K\r\n;sys_temp_dir = \"/tmp\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether or not to enable the dl() function.  The dl() function does NOT work\u001b[K\r\n; properly in multithreaded servers, such as IIS or Zeus, and is automatically\u001b[K\r\n; disabled on them.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/enable-dl\u001b[K\r\nenable_dl =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; cgi.force_redirect is necessary to provide security running PHP as a CGI under\u001b[K\r\n; most web servers.  Left undefined, PHP turns this on by default.  You can\u001b[K\r\n; turn it off here AT YOUR OWN RISK\u001b[K\r\n; **You CAN safely turn this off for IIS, in fact, you MUST.**\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/cgi.force-redirect\u001b[K\r\n;cgi.force_redirect = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; if cgi.nph is enabled it will force cgi to always sent Status: 200 with\u001b[K\r\n; every request. PHP's default behavior is to disable this feature.\u001b[K\r\n;cgi.nph = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; if cgi.force_redirect is turned on, and you are not running under Apache or Netscape\u001b[K\r\n; (iPlanet) web servers, you MAY need to set an environment variable name that PHP\u001b[K\r\n; will look for to know it is OK to continue execution.  Setting this variable MAY\u001b[K\r\n; cause security issues, KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING FIRST.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/cgi.redirect-status-env\u001b[K\r\n;cgi.redirect_status_env =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; cgi.fix_pathinfo provides *real* PATH_INFO/PATH_TRANSLATED support for CGI.  PHP's\u001b[K\r\n; previous behaviour was to set PATH_TRANSLATED to SCRIPT_FILENAME, and to not grok\u001b[K\r\n; what PATH_INFO is.  For more information on PATH_INFO, see the cgi specs.  Setting\u001b[K\r\n; this to 1 will cause PHP CGI to fix its paths to conform to the spec.  A setting\u001b[K\r\n; of zero causes PHP to behave as before.  Default is 1.  You should fix your scripts\u001b[K\r\n; to use SCRIPT_FILENAME rather than PATH_TRANSLATED.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/cgi.fix-pathinfo\u001b[K\r\n;cgi.fix_pathinfo=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f53,23         41\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.283, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; if cgi.discard_path is enabled, the PHP CGI binary can safely be placed outside\u001b[K\r\n; of the web tree and people will not be able to circumvent .htaccess security.\u001b[K\r\n;cgi.discard_path=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; FastCGI under IIS supports the ability to impersonate\u001b[K\r\n; security tokens of the calling client.  This allows IIS to define the\u001b[K\r\n; security context that the request runs under.  mod_fastcgi under Apache\u001b[K\r\n; does not currently support this feature (03/17/2002)\u001b[K\r\n; Set to 1 if running under IIS.  Default is zero.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/fastcgi.impersonate\u001b[K\r\n;fastcgi.impersonate = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Prevent decoding of SCRIPT_FILENAME when using Apache ProxyPass or\u001b[K\r\n; ProxyPassMatch. This should be used if script file paths are not stored\u001b[K\r\n; in an encoded format on the file system.\u001b[K\r\n; Default is 1.\u001b[K\r\n;fastcgi.script_path_encoded = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Disable logging through FastCGI connection. PHP's default behavior is to enable\u001b[K\r\n; this feature.\u001b[K\r\n;fastcgi.logging = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; cgi.rfc2616_headers configuration option tells PHP what type of headers to\u001b[K\r\n; use when sending HTTP response code. If set to 0, PHP sends Status: header that\u001b[K\r\n; is supported by Apache. When this option is set to 1, PHP will send\u001b[K\r\n; RFC2616 compliant header.\u001b[K\r\n; Default is zero.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/cgi.rfc2616-headers\u001b[K\r\n;cgi.rfc2616_headers = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; cgi.check_shebang_line controls whether CGI PHP checks for line starting with #!\u001b[K\r\n; (shebang) at the top of the running script. This line might be needed if the\u001b[K\r\n; script support running both as stand-alone script and via PHP CGI<. PHP in CGI\u001b[K\r\n; mode skips this line and ignores its content if this directive is turned on.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/cgi.check-shebang-line\u001b[K\r\n;cgi.check_shebang_line=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; File Uploads ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether to allow HTTP file uploads.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/file-uploads\u001b[K\r\nfile_uploads =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f97,19         43\u001b[1;19H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.221, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;19H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\n; Temporary directory for HTTP uploaded files (will use system default if not\u001b[K\r\n; specified).\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/upload-tmp-dir\u001b[K\r\n;upload_tmp_dir =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum allowed size for uploaded files.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/upload-max-filesize\u001b[K\r\nupload_max_filesize =\u001b[92m 2M\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum number of files that can be uploaded via a single request\u001b[K\r\nmax_file_uploads = 20\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Fopen wrappers ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether to allow the treatment of URLs (like http:// or ftp://) as files.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/allow-url-fopen\u001b[K\r\nallow_url_fopen =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether to allow include/require to open URLs (like https:// or ftp://) as files.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/allow-url-include\u001b[K\r\nallow_url_include =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Define the anonymous ftp password (your email address). PHP's default setting\u001b[K\r\n; for this is empty.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/from\u001b[K\r\n;from=\"john@doe.com\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Define the User-Agent string. PHP's default setting for this is empty.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/user-agent\u001b[K\r\n;user_agent=\"PHP\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Default timeout for socket based streams (seconds)\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/default-socket-timeout\u001b[K\r\ndefault_socket_timeout = 60\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If your scripts have to deal with files from Macintosh systems,\u001b[K\r\n; or you are running on a Mac and need to deal with files from\u001b[K\r\n; unix or win32 systems, setting this flag will cause PHP to\u001b[K\r\n; automatically detect the EOL character in those files so that\u001b[K\r\n; fgets() and file() will work regardless of the source of the file.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/auto-detect-line-endings\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f841,23         45\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.260, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H;auto_detect_line_endings = Off\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Dynamic Extensions ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\u001b[K\r\n; syntax:\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n;   extension=modulename\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; For example:\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n;   extension=mysqli\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; When the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\u001b[K\r\n; directory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n;   extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; Note : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('extension=<ext>.so' and\u001b[K\r\n; 'extension='php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\u001b[K\r\n; deprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\u001b[K\r\n; move to the new ('extension=<ext>) syntax.\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n;extension=bcmath\u001b[K\r\n;extension=bz2\u001b[K\r\n;extension=calendar\u001b[K\r\nextension=\u001b[92mcurl\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n;extension=dba\u001b[K\r\n;extension=enchant\u001b[K\r\n;extension=exif\u001b[K\r\n;extension=ffi\u001b[K\r\n;extension=ftp\u001b[K\r\n;extension=gd\u001b[K\r\n;extension=gettext\u001b[K\r\n;extension=gmp\u001b[K\r\n;extension=iconv\u001b[K\r\n;extension=intl\u001b[K\r\n;extension=ldap\u001b[K\r\n;extension=mysqli\u001b[K\r\n;extension=odbc\u001b[K\r\n;extension=pdo_dblib\u001b[K\r\n;extension=pdo_mysql\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f85,23         48\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.373, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H;extension=pdo_odbc\u001b[K\r\n;extension=pdo_pgsql\u001b[K\r\n;extension=pdo_sqlite\u001b[K\r\n;extension=pgsql\u001b[K\r\n;extension=shmop\u001b[K\r\n;extension=snmp\u001b[K\r\n;extension=soap\u001b[K\r\n;extension=sockets\u001b[K\r\n;extension=sodium\u001b[K\r\n;extension=sqlite3\u001b[K\r\n;extension=sysvmsg\u001b[K\r\n;extension=sysvsem\u001b[K\r\n;extension=sysvshm\u001b[K\r\n;extension=tidy\u001b[K\r\n;extension=xsl\u001b[K\r\nextension=\u001b[92mzip\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Module Settings ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[CLI Server]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Whether the CLI web server uses ANSI color coding in its terminal output.\u001b[K\r\ncli_server.color =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Date]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Defines the default timezone used by the date functions\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/date.timezone\u001b[K\r\n;date.timezone =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/date.default-latitude\u001b[K\r\n;date.default_latitude = 31.7667\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/date.default-longitude\u001b[K\r\n;date.default_longitude = 35.2333\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/date.sunrise-zenith\u001b[K\r\n;date.sunrise_zenith = 90.833333\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/date.sunset-zenith\u001b[K\r\n;date.sunset_zenith = 90.833333\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[filter]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/filter.default\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f929,20         50\u001b[1;20H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.257, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;20H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[H\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m[\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mfilter\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m]\r\n\n\u001b[m\u000f;filter.default = unsafe_raw\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/filter.default-flags\u001b[K\r\n;filter.default_flags =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[iconv]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global input_encoding instead.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset or input_encoding or iconv.input_encoding is used.\u001b[K\r\n; The precedence is: default_charset < input_encoding < iconv.input_encoding\u001b[K\r\n;iconv.input_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global internal_encoding instead.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset or internal_encoding or iconv.internal_encoding is used.\u001b[K\r\n; The precedence is: default_charset < internal_encoding < iconv.internal_encoding\u001b[K\r\n;iconv.internal_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global output_encoding instead.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset or output_encoding or iconv.output_encoding is used.\u001b[K\r\n; The precedence is: default_charset < output_encoding < iconv.output_encoding\u001b[K\r\n; To use an output encoding conversion, iconv's output handler must be set\u001b[K\r\n; otherwise output encoding conversion cannot be performed.\u001b[K\r\n;iconv.output_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[intl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n;intl.default_locale =\u001b[K\r\n; This directive allows you to produce PHP errors when some error\u001b[K\r\n; happens within intl functions. The value is the level of the error produced.\u001b[K\r\n; Default is 0, which does not produce any errors.\u001b[K\r\n; This directive is deprecated.\u001b[K\r\n;intl.error_level = E_WARNING\u001b[K\r\n; If enabled this directive indicates that when an error occurs within an\u001b[K\r\n; intl function a IntlException should be thrown.\u001b[K\r\n; Default is Off, which means errors need to be handled manually.\u001b[K\r\n;intl.use_exceptions = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[sqlite3]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Directory pointing to SQLite3 extensions\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/sqlite3.extension-dir\u001b[K\r\n;sqlite3.extension_dir =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; SQLite defensive mode flag (only available from SQLite 3.26+)\u001b[K\r\n; When the defensive flag is enabled, language features that allow ordinary\u001b[K\r\n; SQL to deliberately corrupt the database file are disabled. This forbids\u001b[K\r\n; writing directly to the schema, shadow tables (eg. FTS data tables), or\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f73,8          53\u001b[1;8H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.227, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;8H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; the sqlite_dbpage virtual table.\u001b[K\r\n; https://www.sqlite.org/c3ref/c_dbconfig_defensive.html\u001b[K\r\n; (for older SQLite versions, this flag has no use)\u001b[K\r\n;sqlite3.defensive = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Pcre]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; PCRE library backtracking limit.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pcre.backtrack-limit\u001b[K\r\n;pcre.backtrack_limit=100000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; PCRE library recursion limit.\u001b[K\r\n; Please note that if you set this value to a high number you may consume all\u001b[K\r\n; the available process stack and eventually crash PHP (due to reaching the\u001b[K\r\n; stack size limit imposed by the Operating System).\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pcre.recursion-limit\u001b[K\r\n;pcre.recursion_limit=100000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables or disables JIT compilation of patterns. This requires the PCRE\u001b[K\r\n; library to be compiled with JIT support.\u001b[K\r\n;pcre.jit=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Pdo]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Whether to pool ODBC connections. Can be one of \"strict\", \"relaxed\" or \"off\"\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pdo-odbc.connection-pooling\u001b[K\r\n;pdo_odbc.connection_pooling=strict\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Pdo_mysql]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Default socket name for local MySQL connects.  If empty, uses the built-in\u001b[K\r\n; MySQL defaults.\u001b[K\r\npdo_mysql.default_socket=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Phar]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/phar.readonly\u001b[K\r\n;phar.readonly = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/phar.require-hash\u001b[K\r\n;phar.require_hash = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;phar.cache_list =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[mail function]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; For Win32 only.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/smtp\u001b[K\r\nSMTP =\u001b[92m localhost\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f1017,23        55\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.187, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; https://php.net/smtp-port\u001b[K\r\nsmtp_port = 25\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; For Win32 only.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/sendmail-from\u001b[K\r\n;sendmail_from = me@example.com\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; For Unix only.  You may supply arguments as well (default: \"sendmail -t -i\").\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/sendmail-path\u001b[K\r\n;sendmail_path =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Force the addition of the specified parameters to be passed as extra parameters\u001b[K\r\n; to the sendmail binary. These parameters will always replace the value of\u001b[K\r\n; the 5th parameter to mail().\u001b[K\r\n;mail.force_extra_parameters =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Add X-PHP-Originating-Script: that will include uid of the script followed by the filename\u001b[K\r\nmail.add_x_header =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Use mixed LF and CRLF line separators to keep compatibility with some\u001b[K\r\n; RFC 2822 non conformant MTA.\u001b[K\r\nmail.mixed_lf_and_crlf =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Control line ending mode for mail messages and headers.\u001b[K\r\n; Possible values: \"crlf\" (default), \"lf\", \"mixed\", \"os\"\u001b[K\r\n; - crlf: Use CRLF line endings\u001b[K\r\n; - lf: Use LF line endings only (converts CRLF in message to LF)\u001b[K\r\n; - mixed: Same as mail.mixed_lf_and_crlf = On\u001b[K\r\n; - os: Use CRLF on Windows, LF on other systems\u001b[K\r\nmail.cr_lf_mode =\u001b[92m crlf\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The path to a log file that will log all mail() calls. Log entries include\u001b[K\r\n; the full path of the script, line number, To address and headers.\u001b[K\r\n;mail.log =\u001b[K\r\n; Log mail to syslog (Event Log on Windows).\u001b[K\r\n;mail.log = syslog\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[ODBC]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.default-db\u001b[K\r\n;odbc.default_db    =  Not yet implemented\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/odbc.default-user\u001b[K\r\n;odbc.default_user  =  Not yet implemented\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f61,22        57\u001b[1;22H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.190, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;22H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; https://php.net/odbc.default-pw\u001b[K\r\n;odbc.default_pw    =  Not yet implemented\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Controls the ODBC cursor model.\u001b[K\r\n; Default: SQL_CURSOR_STATIC (default).\u001b[K\r\n;odbc.default_cursortype\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allow or prevent persistent links.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.allow-persistent\u001b[K\r\nodbc.allow_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Check that a connection is still valid before reuse.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.check-persistent\u001b[K\r\nodbc.check_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum number of persistent links.  -1 means no limit.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.max-persistent\u001b[K\r\nodbc.max_persistent =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum number of links (persistent + non-persistent).  -1 means no limit.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.max-links\u001b[K\r\nodbc.max_links =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Handling of LONG fields.  Returns number of bytes to variables.  0 means\u001b[K\r\n; passthru.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.defaultlrl\u001b[K\r\nodbc.defaultlrl = 4096\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Handling of binary data.  0 means passthru, 1 return as is, 2 convert to char.\u001b[K\r\n; See the documentation on odbc_binmode and odbc_longreadlen for an explanation\u001b[K\r\n; of odbc.defaultlrl and odbc.defaultbinmode\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.defaultbinmode\u001b[K\r\nodbc.defaultbinmode = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[MySQLi]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum number of persistent links.  -1 means no limit.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.max-persistent\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.max_persistent =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allow accessing, from PHP's perspective, local files with LOAD DATA statements\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.allow_local_infile\u001b[K\r\n;mysqli.allow_local_infile = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f105,23        60\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.405, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; It allows the user to specify a folder where files that can be sent via LOAD DATA\u001b[K\r\n; LOCAL can exist. It is ignored if mysqli.allow_local_infile is enabled.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqli.local_infile_directory =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allow or prevent persistent links.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.allow-persistent\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.allow_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum number of links.  -1 means no limit.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.max-links\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.max_links =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Default port number for mysqli_connect().\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.default-port\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.default_port = 3306\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Default socket name for local MySQL connects.  If empty, uses the built-in\u001b[K\r\n; MySQL defaults.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.default-socket\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.default_socket =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Default host for mysqli_connect().\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.default-host\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.default_host =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Default user for mysqli_connect().\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.default-user\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.default_user =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Default password for mysqli_connect().\u001b[K\r\n; Note that this is generally a *bad* idea to store passwords in this file.\u001b[K\r\n; *Any* user with PHP access can run 'echo get_cfg_var(\"mysqli.default_pw\")\u001b[K\r\n; and reveal this password!  And of course, any users with read access to this\u001b[K\r\n; file will be able to reveal the password as well.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.default-pw\u001b[K\r\nmysqli.default_pw =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If this option is enabled, closing a persistent connection will rollback\u001b[K\r\n; any pending transactions of this connection, before it is put back\u001b[K\r\n; into the persistent connection pool.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqli.rollback_on_cached_plink = Off\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[mysqlnd]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Enable / Disable collection of general statistics by mysqlnd which can be\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f49,23        62\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.423, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[H\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m[\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mmysqlnd\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m]\r\n\n\u001b[m\u000f; used to tune and monitor MySQL operations.\u001b[K\r\nmysqlnd.collect_statistics =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enable / Disable collection of memory usage statistics by mysqlnd which can be\u001b[K\r\n; used to tune and monitor MySQL operations.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: Off\u001b[K\r\nmysqlnd.collect_memory_statistics =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Records communication from all extensions using mysqlnd to the specified log\u001b[K\r\n; file.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mysqlnd.debug\u001b[K\r\n;mysqlnd.debug =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Defines which queries will be logged.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqlnd.log_mask = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Default size of the mysqlnd memory pool, which is used by result sets.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqlnd.mempool_default_size = 16000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Size of a pre-allocated buffer used when sending commands to MySQL in bytes.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqlnd.net_cmd_buffer_size = 2048\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Size of a pre-allocated buffer used for reading data sent by the server in\u001b[K\r\n; bytes.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqlnd.net_read_buffer_size = 32768\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Timeout for network requests in seconds.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqlnd.net_read_timeout = 31536000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; SHA-256 Authentication Plugin related. File with the MySQL server public RSA\u001b[K\r\n; key.\u001b[K\r\n;mysqlnd.sha256_server_public_key =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[PostgreSQL]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Allow or prevent persistent links.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pgsql.allow-persistent\u001b[K\r\npgsql.allow_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Detect broken persistent links always with pg_pconnect().\u001b[K\r\n; Auto reset feature requires a little overheads.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pgsql.auto-reset-persistent\u001b[K\r\npgsql.auto_reset_persistent =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f93,9         65\u001b[1;9H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.265, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;9H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H\u001b[K\n; Maximum number of persistent links.  -1 means no limit.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pgsql.max-persistent\u001b[K\r\npgsql.max_persistent =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Maximum number of links (persistent+non persistent).  -1 means no limit.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pgsql.max-links\u001b[K\r\npgsql.max_links =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Ignore PostgreSQL backends Notice message or not.\u001b[K\r\n; Notice message logging require a little overheads.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pgsql.ignore-notice\u001b[K\r\npgsql.ignore_notice = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Log PostgreSQL backends Notice message or not.\u001b[K\r\n; Unless pgsql.ignore_notice=0, module cannot log notice message.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/pgsql.log-notice\u001b[K\r\npgsql.log_notice = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[bcmath]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Number of decimal digits for all bcmath functions.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/bcmath.scale\u001b[K\r\nbcmath.scale = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[browscap]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/browscap\u001b[K\r\n;browscap = extra/browscap.ini\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Session]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Handler used to store/retrieve data.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.save-handler\u001b[K\r\nsession.save_handler =\u001b[92m files\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Argument passed to save_handler.  In the case of files, this is the path\u001b[K\r\n; where data files are stored. Note: Windows users have to change this\u001b[K\r\n; variable in order to use PHP's session functions.\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; The path can be defined as:\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n;     session.save_path = \"N;/path\"\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; where N is an integer.  Instead of storing all the session files in\u001b[K\r\n; /path, what this will do is use subdirectories N-levels deep, and\u001b[K\r\n; store the session data in those directories.  This is useful if\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f237,23        67\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.319, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; your OS has problems with many files in one directory, and is\u001b[K\r\n; a more efficient layout for servers that handle many sessions.\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; NOTE 1: PHP will not create this directory structure automatically.\u001b[K\r\n;         You can use the script in the ext/session dir for that purpose.\u001b[K\r\n; NOTE 2: See the section on garbage collection below if you choose to\u001b[K\r\n;         use subdirectories for session storage\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; The file storage module creates files using mode 600 by default.\u001b[K\r\n; You can change that by using\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n;     session.save_path = \"N;MODE;/path\"\u001b[K\r\n;\u001b[K\r\n; where MODE is the octal representation of the mode. Note that this\u001b[K\r\n; does not overwrite the process's umask.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.save-path\u001b[K\r\n;session.save_path = \"/tmp\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether to use strict session mode.\u001b[K\r\n; Strict session mode does not accept an uninitialized session ID, and\u001b[K\r\n; regenerates the session ID if the browser sends an uninitialized session ID.\u001b[K\r\n; Strict mode protects applications from session fixation via a session adoption\u001b[K\r\n; vulnerability. It is disabled by default for maximum compatibility, but\u001b[K\r\n; enabling it is encouraged.\u001b[K\r\n; https://wiki.php.net/rfc/strict_sessions\u001b[K\r\nsession.use_strict_mode = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether to use cookies.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.use-cookies\u001b[K\r\nsession.use_cookies = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-secure\u001b[K\r\n;session.cookie_secure =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-partitioned\u001b[K\r\n;session.cookie_partitioned = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This option forces PHP to fetch and use a cookie for storing and maintaining\u001b[K\r\n; the session id. We encourage this operation as it's very helpful in combating\u001b[K\r\n; session hijacking when not specifying and managing your own session id. It is\u001b[K\r\n; not the be-all and end-all of session hijacking defense, but it's a good start.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.use-only-cookies\u001b[K\r\nsession.use_only_cookies = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f81,23        69\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.343, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Name of the session (used as cookie name).\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.name\u001b[K\r\nsession.name =\u001b[92m PHPSESSID\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Initialize session on request startup.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.auto-start\u001b[K\r\nsession.auto_start = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Lifetime in seconds of cookie or, if 0, until browser is restarted.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-lifetime\u001b[K\r\nsession.cookie_lifetime = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The path for which the cookie is valid.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-path\u001b[K\r\nsession.cookie_path =\u001b[92m /\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The domain for which the cookie is valid.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-domain\u001b[K\r\nsession.cookie_domain =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Whether or not to add the httpOnly flag to the cookie, which makes it\u001b[K\r\n; inaccessible to browser scripting languages such as JavaScript.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-httponly\u001b[K\r\nsession.cookie_httponly =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Add SameSite attribute to cookie to help mitigate Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF/XSRF)\u001b[K\r\n; Current valid values are \"Strict\", \"Lax\" or \"None\". When using \"None\",\u001b[K\r\n; make sure to include the quotes, as `none` is interpreted like `false` in ini files.\u001b[K\r\n; https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-west-first-party-cookies-07\u001b[K\r\nsession.cookie_samesite =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Handler used to serialize data. php is the standard serializer of PHP.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.serialize-handler\u001b[K\r\nsession.serialize_handler =\u001b[92m php\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Defines the probability that the 'garbage collection' process is started on every\u001b[K\r\n; session initialization. The probability is calculated by using gc_probability/gc_divisor,\u001b[K\r\n; e.g. 1/100 means there is a 1% chance that the GC process starts on each request.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.gc-probability\u001b[K\r\nsession.gc_probability = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f325,23        72\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.354, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Defines the probability that the 'garbage collection' process is started on every\u001b[K\r\n; session initialization. The probability is calculated by using gc_probability/gc_divisor,\u001b[K\r\n; e.g. 1/100 means there is a 1% chance that the GC process starts on each request.\u001b[K\r\n; For high volume production servers, using a value of 1000 is a more efficient approach.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: 100\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: 1000\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: 1000\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.gc-divisor\u001b[K\r\nsession.gc_divisor = 1000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; After this number of seconds, stored data will be seen as 'garbage' and\u001b[K\r\n; cleaned up by the garbage collection process.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.gc-maxlifetime\u001b[K\r\nsession.gc_maxlifetime = 1440\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; NOTE: If you are using the subdirectory option for storing session files\u001b[K\r\n;       (see session.save_path above), then garbage collection does *not*\u001b[K\r\n;       happen automatically.  You will need to do your own garbage\u001b[K\r\n;       collection through a shell script, cron entry, or some other method.\u001b[K\r\n;       For example, the following script is the equivalent of setting\u001b[K\r\n;       session.gc_maxlifetime to 1440 (1440 seconds = 24 minutes):\u001b[K\r\n;          find /path/to/sessions -cmin +24 -type f | xargs rm\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Check HTTP Referer to invalidate externally stored URLs containing ids.\u001b[K\r\n; HTTP_REFERER has to contain this substring for the session to be\u001b[K\r\n; considered as valid.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.referer-check\u001b[K\r\nsession.referer_check =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Set to {nocache,private,public,} to determine HTTP caching aspects\u001b[K\r\n; or leave this empty to avoid sending anti-caching headers.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.cache-limiter\u001b[K\r\nsession.cache_limiter =\u001b[92m nocache\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Document expires after n minutes.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.cache-expire\u001b[K\r\nsession.cache_expire = 180\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; trans sid support is disabled by default.\u001b[K\r\n; Use of trans sid may risk your users' security.\u001b[K\r\n; Use this option with caution.\u001b[K\r\n; - User may send URL contains active session ID\u001b[K\r\n;   to other person via. email/irc/etc.\u001b[K\r\n; - URL that contains active session ID may be stored\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f69,23        74\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.230, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H;   in publicly accessible computer.\u001b[K\r\n; - User may access your site with the same session ID\u001b[K\r\n;   always using URL stored in browser's history or bookmarks.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.use-trans-sid\u001b[K\r\nsession.use_trans_sid = 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The URL rewriter will look for URLs in a defined set of HTML tags.\u001b[K\r\n; <form> is special; if you include them here, the rewriter will\u001b[K\r\n; add a hidden <input> field with the info which is otherwise appended\u001b[K\r\n; to URLs. <form> tag's action attribute URL will not be modified\u001b[K\r\n; unless it is specified.\u001b[K\r\n; Note that all valid entries require a \"=\", even if no value follows.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/url-rewriter.tags\u001b[K\r\nsession.trans_sid_tags =\u001b[92m \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; URL rewriter does not rewrite absolute URLs by default.\u001b[K\r\n; To enable rewrites for absolute paths, target hosts must be specified\u001b[K\r\n; at RUNTIME. i.e. use ini_set()\u001b[K\r\n; <form> tags is special. PHP will check action attribute's URL regardless\u001b[K\r\n; of session.trans_sid_tags setting.\u001b[K\r\n; If no host is defined, HTTP_HOST will be used for allowed host.\u001b[K\r\n; Example value: php.net,www.php.net,wiki.php.net\u001b[K\r\n; Use \",\" for multiple hosts. No spaces are allowed.\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"\"\u001b[K\r\n;session.trans_sid_hosts=\"\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enable upload progress tracking in $_SESSION\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.enabled\u001b[K\r\n;session.upload_progress.enabled = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Cleanup the progress information as soon as all POST data has been read\u001b[K\r\n; (i.e. upload completed).\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: On\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.cleanup\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f413,23        77\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.242, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H;session.upload_progress.cleanup = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; A prefix used for the upload progress key in $_SESSION\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"upload_progress_\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"upload_progress_\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"upload_progress_\"\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.prefix\u001b[K\r\n;session.upload_progress.prefix = \"upload_progress_\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The index name (concatenated with the prefix) in $_SESSION\u001b[K\r\n; containing the upload progress information\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.name\u001b[K\r\n;session.upload_progress.name = \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; How frequently the upload progress should be updated.\u001b[K\r\n; Given either in percentages (per-file), or in bytes\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: \"1%\"\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: \"1%\"\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: \"1%\"\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.freq\u001b[K\r\n;session.upload_progress.freq =  \"1%\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The minimum delay between updates, in seconds\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n; Development Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.min-freq\u001b[K\r\n;session.upload_progress.min_freq = \"1\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Only write session data when session data is changed. Enabled by default.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/session.lazy-write\u001b[K\r\n;session.lazy_write = On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Assertion]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Switch whether to compile assertions at all (to have no overhead at run-time)\u001b[K\r\n; -1: Do not compile at all\u001b[K\r\n;  0: Jump over assertion at run-time\u001b[K\r\n;  1: Execute assertions\u001b[K\r\n; Changing from or to a negative value is only possible in php.ini!\u001b[K\r\n; (For turning assertions on and off at run-time, toggle zend.assertions between the values 1 and 0)\u001b[K\r\n; Default Value: 1\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f57,22        79\u001b[1;22H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.236, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;22H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Development Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n; Production Value: -1\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/zend.assertions\u001b[K\r\nzend.assertions =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[COM]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; path to a file containing GUIDs, IIDs or filenames of files with TypeLibs\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/com.typelib-file\u001b[K\r\n;com.typelib_file =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; allow Distributed-COM calls\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/com.allow-dcom\u001b[K\r\n;com.allow_dcom = true\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; autoregister constants of a component's typelib on com_load()\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/com.autoregister-typelib\u001b[K\r\n;com.autoregister_typelib = true\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; register constants casesensitive\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/com.autoregister-casesensitive\u001b[K\r\n;com.autoregister_casesensitive = false\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; show warnings on duplicate constant registrations\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/com.autoregister-verbose\u001b[K\r\n;com.autoregister_verbose = true\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The default character set code-page to use when passing strings to and from COM objects.\u001b[K\r\n; Default: system ANSI code page\u001b[K\r\n;com.code_page=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The version of the .NET framework to use. The value of the setting are the first three parts\u001b[K\r\n; of the framework's version number, separated by dots, and prefixed with \"v\", e.g. \"v4.0.30319\".\u001b[K\r\n;com.dotnet_version=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[mbstring]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; language for internal character representation.\u001b[K\r\n; This affects mb_send_mail() and mbstring.detect_order.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.language\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.language = Japanese\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global internal_encoding instead.\u001b[K\r\n; internal/script encoding.\u001b[K\r\n; Some encoding cannot work as internal encoding. (e.g. SJIS, BIG5, ISO-2022-*)\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset or internal_encoding or iconv.internal_encoding is used.\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f501,23        82\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.234, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; The precedence is: default_charset < internal_encoding < iconv.internal_encoding\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.internal_encoding =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global input_encoding instead.\u001b[K\r\n; http input encoding.\u001b[K\r\n; mbstring.encoding_translation = On is needed to use this setting.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset or input_encoding or mbstring.input is used.\u001b[K\r\n; The precedence is: default_charset < input_encoding < mbstring.http_input\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.http-input\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.http_input =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global output_encoding instead.\u001b[K\r\n; http output encoding.\u001b[K\r\n; mb_output_handler must be registered as output buffer to function.\u001b[K\r\n; If empty, default_charset or output_encoding or mbstring.http_output is used.\u001b[K\r\n; The precedence is: default_charset < output_encoding < mbstring.http_output\u001b[K\r\n; To use an output encoding conversion, mbstring's output handler must be set\u001b[K\r\n; otherwise output encoding conversion cannot be performed.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.http-output\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.http_output =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; enable automatic encoding translation according to\u001b[K\r\n; mbstring.internal_encoding setting. Input chars are\u001b[K\r\n; converted to internal encoding by setting this to On.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: Do _not_ use automatic encoding translation for\u001b[K\r\n;       portable libs/applications.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.encoding-translation\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.encoding_translation = Off\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; automatic encoding detection order.\u001b[K\r\n; \"auto\" detect order is changed according to mbstring.language\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.detect-order\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.detect_order = auto\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; substitute_character used when character cannot be converted\u001b[K\r\n; one from another\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.substitute-character\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.substitute_character = none\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enable strict encoding detection.\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.strict_detection = Off\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive specifies the regex pattern of content types for which mb_output_handler()\u001b[K\r\n; is activated.\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f45,23        84\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.228, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Default: mbstring.http_output_conv_mimetypes=^(text/|application/xhtml\\+xml)\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.http_output_conv_mimetypes=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive specifies maximum stack depth for mbstring regular expressions. It is similar\u001b[K\r\n; to the pcre.recursion_limit for PCRE.\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.regex_stack_limit=100000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; This directive specifies maximum retry count for mbstring regular expressions. It is similar\u001b[K\r\n; to the pcre.backtrack_limit for PCRE.\u001b[K\r\n;mbstring.regex_retry_limit=1000000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[gd]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Tell the jpeg decode to ignore warnings and try to create\u001b[K\r\n; a gd image. The warning will then be displayed as notices\u001b[K\r\n; disabled by default\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/gd.jpeg-ignore-warning\u001b[K\r\n;gd.jpeg_ignore_warning = 1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[exif]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Exif UNICODE user comments are handled as UCS-2BE/UCS-2LE and JIS as JIS.\u001b[K\r\n; With mbstring support this will automatically be converted into the encoding\u001b[K\r\n; given by corresponding encode setting. When empty mbstring.internal_encoding\u001b[K\r\n; is used. For the decode settings you can distinguish between motorola and\u001b[K\r\n; intel byte order. A decode setting must not be empty.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/exif.encode-unicode\u001b[K\r\n;exif.encode_unicode = ISO-8859-15\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/exif.decode-unicode-motorola\u001b[K\r\n;exif.decode_unicode_motorola = UCS-2BE\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/exif.decode-unicode-intel\u001b[K\r\n;exif.decode_unicode_intel    = UCS-2LE\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/exif.encode-jis\u001b[K\r\n;exif.encode_jis =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/exif.decode-jis-motorola\u001b[K\r\n;exif.decode_jis_motorola = JIS\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; https://php.net/exif.decode-jis-intel\u001b[K\r\n;exif.decode_jis_intel    = JIS\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[Tidy]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; The path to a default tidy configuration file to use when using tidy\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f89,23        86\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.231, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[H\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m[\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mTidy\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m]\r\n\n\u001b[m\u000f; https://php.net/tidy.default-config\u001b[K\r\n;tidy.default_config = /usr/local/lib/php/default.tcfg\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Should tidy clean and repair output automatically?\u001b[K\r\n; WARNING: Do not use this option if you are generating non-html content\u001b[K\r\n; such as dynamic images\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/tidy.clean-output\u001b[K\r\ntidy.clean_output =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[soap]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Enables or disables WSDL caching feature.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/soap.wsdl-cache-enabled\u001b[K\r\nsoap.wsdl_cache_enabled=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Sets the directory name where SOAP extension will put cache files.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/soap.wsdl-cache-dir\u001b[K\r\nsoap.wsdl_cache_dir=\u001b[92m\"/tmp\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; (time to live) Sets the number of second while cached file will be used\u001b[K\r\n; instead of original one.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/soap.wsdl-cache-ttl\u001b[K\r\nsoap.wsdl_cache_ttl=86400\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Sets the size of the cache limit. (Max. number of WSDL files to cache)\u001b[K\r\nsoap.wsdl_cache_limit = 5\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[sysvshm]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; A default size of the shared memory segment\u001b[K\r\n;sysvshm.init_mem = 10000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[ldap]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Sets the maximum number of open links or -1 for unlimited.\u001b[K\r\nldap.max_links =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[dba]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n;dba.default_handler=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[opcache]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; Determines if Zend OPCache is enabled\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.enable=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Determines if Zend OPCache is enabled for the CLI version of PHP\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.enable_cli=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f633,6         89\u001b[1;6H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.185, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;6H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; The OPcache shared memory storage size.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.memory_consumption=128\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The amount of memory for interned strings in Mbytes.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.interned_strings_buffer=8\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The maximum number of keys (scripts) in the OPcache hash table.\u001b[K\r\n; Only numbers between 200 and 1000000 are allowed.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.max_accelerated_files=10000\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The maximum percentage of \"wasted\" memory until a restart is scheduled.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.max_wasted_percentage=5\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; When this directive is enabled, the OPcache appends the current working\u001b[K\r\n; directory to the script key, thus eliminating possible collisions between\u001b[K\r\n; files with the same name (basename). Disabling the directive improves\u001b[K\r\n; performance, but may break existing applications.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.use_cwd=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; When disabled, you must reset the OPcache manually or restart the\u001b[K\r\n; webserver for changes to the filesystem to take effect.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.validate_timestamps=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; How often (in seconds) to check file timestamps for changes to the shared\u001b[K\r\n; memory storage allocation. (\"1\" means validate once per second, but only\u001b[K\r\n; once per request. \"0\" means always validate)\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.revalidate_freq=2\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables or disables file search in include_path optimization\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.revalidate_path=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If disabled, all PHPDoc comments are dropped from the code to reduce the\u001b[K\r\n; size of the optimized code.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.save_comments=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If enabled, compilation warnings (including notices and deprecations) will\u001b[K\r\n; be recorded and replayed each time a file is included. Otherwise, compilation\u001b[K\r\n; warnings will only be emitted when the file is first cached.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.record_warnings=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allow file existence override (file_exists, etc.) performance feature.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.enable_file_override=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; A bitmask, where each bit enables or disables the appropriate OPcache\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f77,21        91\u001b[1;21H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.387, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;21H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; passes\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.optimization_level=0x7FFFBFFF\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;opcache.dups_fix=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The location of the OPcache blacklist file (wildcards allowed).\u001b[K\r\n; Each OPcache blacklist file is a text file that holds the names of files\u001b[K\r\n; that should not be accelerated. The file format is to add each filename\u001b[K\r\n; to a new line. The filename may be a full path or just a file prefix\u001b[K\r\n; (i.e., /var/www/x  blacklists all the files and directories in /var/www\u001b[K\r\n; that start with 'x'). Line starting with a ; are ignored (comments).\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.blacklist_filename=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allows exclusion of large files from being cached. By default all files\u001b[K\r\n; are cached.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.max_file_size=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; How long to wait (in seconds) for a scheduled restart to begin if the cache\u001b[K\r\n; is not being accessed.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.force_restart_timeout=180\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; OPcache error_log file name. Empty string assumes \"stderr\".\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.error_log=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; All OPcache errors go to the Web server log.\u001b[K\r\n; By default, only fatal errors (level 0) or errors (level 1) are logged.\u001b[K\r\n; You can also enable warnings (level 2), info messages (level 3) or\u001b[K\r\n; debug messages (level 4).\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.log_verbosity_level=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Preferred Shared Memory back-end. Leave empty and let the system decide.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.preferred_memory_model=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Protect the shared memory from unexpected writing during script execution.\u001b[K\r\n; Useful for internal debugging only.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.protect_memory=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Allows calling OPcache API functions only from PHP scripts which path is\u001b[K\r\n; started from specified string. The default \"\" means no restriction\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.restrict_api=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Mapping base of shared memory segments (for Windows only). All the PHP\u001b[K\r\n; processes have to map shared memory into the same address space. This\u001b[K\r\n; directive allows to manually fix the \"Unable to reattach to base address\"\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f721,0-1       94\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.254, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; errors.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.mmap_base=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Facilitates multiple OPcache instances per user (for Windows only). All PHP\u001b[K\r\n; processes with the same cache ID and user share an OPcache instance.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.cache_id=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables and sets the second level cache directory.\u001b[K\r\n; It should improve performance when SHM memory is full, at server restart or\u001b[K\r\n; SHM reset. The default \"\" disables file based caching.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.file_cache=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables or disables read-only mode for the second level cache directory.\u001b[K\r\n; It should improve performance for read-only containers,\u001b[K\r\n; when the cache is pre-warmed and packaged alongside the application.\u001b[K\r\n; Best used with `opcache.validate_timestamps=0`, `opcache.enable_file_override=1`\u001b[K\r\n; and `opcache.file_cache_consistency_checks=0`.\u001b[K\r\n; Note: A cache generated with a different build of PHP, a different file path,\u001b[K\r\n; or different settings (including which extensions are loaded), may be ignored.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.file_cache_read_only=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables or disables opcode caching in shared memory.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.file_cache_only=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables or disables checksum validation when script loaded from file cache.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.file_cache_consistency_checks=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Implies opcache.file_cache_only=1 for a certain process that failed to\u001b[K\r\n; reattach to the shared memory (for Windows only). Explicitly enabled file\u001b[K\r\n; cache is required.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.file_cache_fallback=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Enables or disables copying of PHP code (text segment) into HUGE PAGES.\u001b[K\r\n; Under certain circumstances (if only a single global PHP process is\u001b[K\r\n; started from which all others fork), this can increase performance\u001b[K\r\n; by a tiny amount because TLB misses are reduced.  On the other hand, this\u001b[K\r\n; delays PHP startup, increases memory usage and degrades performance\u001b[K\r\n; under memory pressure - use with care.\u001b[K\r\n; Requires appropriate OS configuration.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.huge_code_pages=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Validate cached file permissions.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.validate_permission=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f65,23        96\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.212, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; Prevent name collisions in chroot'ed environment.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.validate_root=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If specified, it produces opcode dumps for debugging different stages of\u001b[K\r\n; optimizations.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.opt_debug_level=0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Specifies a PHP script that is going to be compiled and executed at server\u001b[K\r\n; start-up.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/opcache.preload\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.preload=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Preloading code as root is not allowed for security reasons. This directive\u001b[K\r\n; facilitates to let the preloading to be run as another user.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/opcache.preload_user\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.preload_user=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Prevents caching files that are less than this number of seconds old. It\u001b[K\r\n; protects from caching of incompletely updated files. In case all file updates\u001b[K\r\n; on your site are atomic, you may increase performance by setting it to \"0\".\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.file_update_protection=2\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Absolute path used to store shared lockfiles (for *nix only).\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.lockfile_path=/tmp\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[curl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; A default value for the CURLOPT_CAINFO option. This is required to be an\u001b[K\r\n; absolute path.\u001b[K\r\n;curl.cainfo =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[openssl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; The location of a Certificate Authority (CA) file on the local filesystem\u001b[K\r\n; to use when verifying the identity of SSL/TLS peers. Most users should\u001b[K\r\n; not specify a value for this directive as PHP will attempt to use the\u001b[K\r\n; OS-managed cert stores in its absence. If specified, this value may still\u001b[K\r\n; be overridden on a per-stream basis via the \"cafile\" SSL stream context\u001b[K\r\n; option.\u001b[K\r\n;openssl.cafile=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If openssl.cafile is not specified or if the CA file is not found, the\u001b[K\r\n; directory pointed to by openssl.capath is searched for a suitable\u001b[K\r\n; certificate. This value must be a correctly hashed certificate directory.\u001b[K\r\n; Most users should not specify a value for this directive as PHP will\u001b[K\r\n; attempt to use the OS-managed cert stores in its absence. If specified,\u001b[K\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f809,23        98\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.280, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[44M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[3;1H; this value may still be overridden on a per-stream basis via the \"capath\"\u001b[K\r\n; SSL stream context option.\u001b[K\r\n;openssl.capath=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The libctx is an OpenSSL library context. OpenSSL defines a default library\u001b[K\r\n; context, but PHP OpenSSL also defines its own library context to avoid\u001b[K\r\n; interference with other libraries using OpenSSL and to provide an independent\u001b[K\r\n; context for each thread in ZTS. Possible values:\u001b[K\r\n;  \"custom\"  - use a custom library context (default)\u001b[K\r\n;  \"default\" - use the default OpenSSL library context\u001b[K\r\n;openssl.libctx=custom\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[ffi]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; FFI API restriction. Possible values:\u001b[K\r\n; \"preload\" - enabled in CLI scripts and preloaded files (default)\u001b[K\r\n; \"false\"   - always disabled\u001b[K\r\n; \"true\"    - always enabled\u001b[K\r\n;ffi.enable=preload\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; List of headers files to preload, wildcard patterns allowed.\u001b[K\r\n;ffi.preload=\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\r\n~\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f53,23        Bot\u001b[1;23H\u001b[?25h"]
