[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;2H protects from caching of incompletely updated files. In case all file updates\r\n; on your site are atomic, you may increase performance by setting it to \"0\".\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.file_update_protection=2\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Absolute path used to store shared lockfiles (for *nix only).\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.lockfile_path=/tmp\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[curl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; A default value for the CURLOPT_CAINFO option. This is required to be an\u001b[K\r\n; absolute path.\u001b[K\r\n;curl.cainfo =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[openssl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; The location of a Certificate Authority (CA) file on the local filesystem\u001b[K\r\n; to use when verifying the identity of SSL/TLS peers. Most users should\u001b[K\r\n; not specify a value for this directive as PHP will attempt to use the\u001b[K\r\n; OS-managed cert stores in its absence. If specified, this value may still\u001b[K\r\n; be overridden on a per-stream basis via the \"cafile\" SSL stream context\u001b[K\r\n; option.\u001b[K\r\n;openssl.cafile=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; If openssl.cafile is not specified or if the CA file is not found, the\u001b[K\r\n; directory pointed to by openssl.capath is searched for a suitable\u001b[K\r\n; certificate. This value must be a correctly hashed certificate directory.\u001b[K\r\n; Most users should not specify a value for this directive as PHP will\u001b[K\r\n; attempt to use the OS-managed cert stores in its absence. If specified,\u001b[K\r\n; this value may still be overridden on a per-stream basis via the \"capath\"\u001b[K\r\n; SSL stream context option.\u001b[K\r\n;openssl.capath=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The libctx is an OpenSSL library context. OpenSSL defines a default library\u001b[K\r\n; context, but PHP OpenSSL also defines its own library context to avoid\u001b[K\r\n; interference with other libraries using OpenSSL and to provide an independent\u001b[K\r\n; context for each thread in ZTS. Possible values:\u001b[K\r\n;  \"custom\"  - use a custom library context (default)\u001b[K\r\n;  \"default\" - use the default OpenSSL library context\u001b[K\r\n;openssl.libctx=custom\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n\u001b[96m[ffi]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n; FFI API restriction. Possible values:\u001b[K\r\n; \"preload\" - enabled in CLI scripts and preloaded files (default)\u001b[K\r\n; \"false\"   - always disabled\u001b[K\r\n; \"true\"    - always enabled\u001b[K\r\n;ffi.enable=preload\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; List of headers files to preload, wildcard patterns allowed.\u001b[K\u001b[47;156H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f4,23        99%\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.928, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hor different settings (including which extensions are loaded), may be ignored.\u001b[2;2Hopcache.file_cache_read_only=0\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[33X\n; Enables or disables opcode caching in shared memory.\u001b[5;2Hopcache.file_cache_only=0\u001b[37X\r\n\u001b[27X\n; Enables or disables checksum validation when script loaded from file cache.\r\n;opcache.file_cache_consistency_checks=1\r\n\u001b[74X\u001b[10;3HImplies opcache.file_cache_only=1 for a certain process that failed to\u001b[11;2H reattach to the shared memory (for Windows only). Explicitly enabled file\r\n; cache is required.\r\n;opcache.file_cache_fallback=1\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[15;3HEnables or disables copying of PHP code (text segment) into HUGE PAGES.\u001b[16;3HUnder certain circumstances (if only a single global PHP process is  \u001b[17;3Hstarted from which all others fork), this can increase performance\u001b[7X\u001b[18;4Hy a tiny amount because TLB misses are reduced.  On the other hand, this\u001b[19;3Hdelays PHP startup, increases memory usage and degrades performance\u001b[20;2H under memory pressure - use with care.\r\n; Requires appropriate OS configuration.\u001b[22;2Hopcache.huge_code_pages=0\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[67X\u001b[24;3HValidate cached file permissions.\u001b[40X\u001b[25;2Hopcache.validate_permission=0\u001b[40X\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[27;3HPrevent name collisions in chroot'ed environment.\u001b[24X\u001b[28;2Hopcache.validate_root=0    \r\n\u001b[16X\n; If specified, it produces opcode dumps for debugging different stages of\u001b[31;3Hoptimizations.\u001b[61X\u001b[32;2Hopcache.opt_debug_level=0\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[79X\u001b[34;3HSpecifies a PHP script that is going to be compiled and executed at server\u001b[35;3Hstart-up.\u001b[42X\u001b[36;3Hhttps://php.net/opcache.preload\u001b[21X\u001b[37;4Hcache.preload=\u001b[5X\r\n\n; Preloading code as root is not allowed for security reasons. This directive\u001b[40;3Hfacilitates to let the preloading to be run as another user.\u001b[41;3Hhttps://php.net/opcache.preload_user\u001b[28X\u001b[42;2Hopcache.preload_user=\u001b[7X\r\n\u001b[28X\u001b[44;2H Prevents caching files that are less than this number of seconds old. It\r\n; protects from caching of incompletely updated files. In case all file updates\u001b[46;3Hon your site are atomic, you may increase performance by setting it to \"0\".\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f30,23        97\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.496, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3His not being accessed.\u001b[56X\u001b[2;11Horce_restart_timeout=180\u001b[4;3HOPcache error_log file name. Empty string assumes \"stderr\".\u001b[5;10Herror_log=\u001b[7X\u001b[7;3HAll OPcache errors go to the Web server log.\u001b[31X\u001b[8;2H By default, only fatal errors (level 0) or errors (level 1) are logged.\r\n; You can also enable warnings (level 2), info messages (level 3) or\u001b[10;3Hdebug messages (level 4).\u001b[45X\u001b[11;2Hopcache.log_verbosity_level=1\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[20X\u001b[13;2H Preferred Shared Memory back-end. Leave empty and let the system decide.\r\n;opcache.preferred_memory_model=\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[16;3HProtect the shared memory from unexpected writing during script execution.\u001b[17;3HUseful for internal debugging only.\u001b[31X\u001b[18;2Hopcache.protect_memory=0\u001b[50X\r\n\u001b[69X\u001b[20;3HAllows calling OPcache API functions only from PHP scripts which path is\u001b[21;3Hstarted from specified string. The default \"\" means no restriction\u001b[22;10Hrestrict_api=    \u001b[24;3HMapping base of shared memory segments (for Windows only). All the PHP\u001b[25;2H processes have to map shared memory into the same address space. This\r\n; directive allows to manually fix the \"Unable to reattach to base address\"\u001b[27;3Herrors.\u001b[42X\nmmap_base=\u001b[5X\u001b[30;3HFacilitates multiple OPcache instances per user (for Windows only). All PHP\u001b[31;3Hprocesses with the same cache ID and user share an OPcache instance.\u001b[32;10Hcache_id=\u001b[8X\u001b[34;3HEnables and sets the second level cache directory.\u001b[24X\u001b[35;3HIt should improve performance when SHM memory is full, at server restart or\u001b[36;3HSHM reset. The default \"\" disables file based caching.\u001b[37;10Hfile_cache=\u001b[39;3HEnables or disables read-only mode for the second level cache directory.   \u001b[40;3HIt should improve performance for read-only containers,\u001b[5X\u001b[41;3Hwhen the cache is pre-warmed and packaged alongside the application.\u001b[42;2H Best used with `opcache.validate_timestamps=0`, `opcache.enable_file_override=1`\r\n; and `opcache.file_cache_consistency_checks=0`.\u001b[44;3HNote: A cache generated with a different build of PHP, a different file path,\u001b[45;3Hor different settings (including which extensions are loaded), may be ignored.\u001b[46;2Hopcache.file_cache_read_only=0\u001b[46X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f786,23        95\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[2.072, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H\u001b[24X\u001b[2;2H When disabled, you must reset the OPcache manually or restart the\r\n; webserver for changes to the filesystem to take effect.\u001b[4;2Hopcache.validate_timestamps=1\u001b[31X\r\n\u001b[19X\n; How often (in seconds) to check file timestamps for changes to the shared\u001b[7;3Hmemory storage allocation. (\"1\" means validate once per second, but only\u001b[8;3Honce per request. \"0\" means always validate)\u001b[27X\u001b[9;2Hopcache.revalidate_freq=2\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[27X\u001b[11;2H Enables or disables file search in include_path optimization\r\n;opcache.revalidate_path=0\r\n\u001b[74X\u001b[14;2H If disabled, all PHPDoc comments are dropped from the code to reduce the\r\n; size of the optimized code.\u001b[16;2Hopcache.save_comments=1\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[37X\u001b[18;2H If enabled, compilation warnings (including notices and deprecations) will\r\n; be recorded and replayed each time a file is included. Otherwise, compilation\u001b[20;3Hwarnings will only be emitted when the file is first cached.\u001b[12X\u001b[21;2Hopcache.record_warnings=0\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[22X\n; Allow file existence override (file_exists, etc.) performance feature.\u001b[24;2Hopcache.enable_file_override=0\u001b[41X\r\n\u001b[71X\u001b[26;3HA bitmask, where each bit enables or disables the appropriate OPcache    \u001b[27;3Hpasses \noptimization_level=0x7FFFBFFF\u001b[30;2Hopcache.dups_fix=0\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[70X\u001b[32;2H The location of the OPcache blacklist file (wildcards allowed).\r\n; Each OPcache blacklist file is a text file that holds the names of files\u001b[34;3Hthat should not be accelerated. The file format is to add each filename\u001b[35;3Hto a new line. The filename may be a full path or just a file prefix\u001b[7X\u001b[36;3H(i.e., /var/www/x  blacklists all the files and directories in /var/www\u001b[37;2H that start with 'x'). Line starting with a ; are ignored (comments).\r\n;opcache.blacklist_filename=\r\n\u001b[74X\u001b[40;3HAllows exclusion of large files from being cached. By default all files\u001b[41;3Hare cached.\u001b[57X\u001b[42;2Hopcache.max_file_size=0\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[48X\u001b[44;3HHow long to wait (in seconds) for a scheduled restart to begin if the cache  \u001b[45;3His not being accessed.\u001b[56X\u001b[46;11Horce_restart_timeout=180\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f42,23        92\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[7.559, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f/\u001b[46;23H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H \r\u001b[48;1H/\u001b[?112c\u001b[?1002l\u001b[?1006l\u001b[?25h"]
[1.041, "o", "\u001b[?25le"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[2;5H\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fn disabl\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd, you must r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000ft th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f OPcach\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f manually or r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fstart th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[3;4He\u001b[m\u000fbs\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000frv\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fr for chang\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs to th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fsyst\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fm to tak\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fff\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[4;8He\u001b[m\u000f.validat\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_tim\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[6;10He\u001b[m\u000fn (in s\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fconds) to ch\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fck fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f tim\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fstamps for chang\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs to th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f shar\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[7;4He\u001b[m\u000fmory storag\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f allocation. (\"1\" m\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fans validat\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f onc\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f p\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fr s\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[8;6He\u001b[m\u000f p\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fr r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fqu\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fst. \"0\" m\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fans always validat\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[9;8He\u001b[m\u000f.r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fvalidat\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_fr\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[11;8He\u001b[m\u000fs or disabl\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f s\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000farch in includ\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[12;8He\u001b[m\u000f.r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fvalidat\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[14;12He\u001b[m\u000fd, all PHPDoc comm\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fnts ar\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f dropp\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd from th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f cod\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f to r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fduc\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[15;6He\u001b[m\u000f of th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f optimiz\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd cod\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[16;8He\u001b[m\u000f.sav\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_comm\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[18;6He\u001b[m\u000fnabl\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd, compilation warnings (including notic\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs and d\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fpr\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[19;4He\u001b[m\u000f r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fcord\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd and r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fplay\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fach tim\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f a fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f is includ\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd. Oth\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000frwis\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[20;23He\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fmitt\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd wh\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fn th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f is first cach\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[21;8He\u001b[m\u000f.r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\n\ne\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fxist\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fnc\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f ov\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000frrid\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f (fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fxists, \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000ftc.) p\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000frformanc\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f f\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fatur\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[24;8He\u001b[m\u000f.\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fnabl\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_ov\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000frrid\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[26;16He\u001b[m\u000fr\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fach bit \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fnabl\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs or disabl\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f appropriat\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f OPcach\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[27;7He\ne\u001b[m\u000f.optimization_l\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fv\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[30;8He\u001b[32;5He\u001b[m\u000f location of th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f OPcach\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f blacklist fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f (wildcards allow\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[33;14He\u001b[m\u000f blacklist fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f is a t\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fxt fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f that holds th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f nam\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs of fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[34;20He\u001b[m\u000f acc\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fl\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000frat\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd. Th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f format is to add \u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fach fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fnam\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[35;9He\u001b[m\u000fw lin\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f. Th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fnam\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f may b\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f a full path or just a fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f pr\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[36;6He\u001b[m\u000f., /var/www/x  blacklists all th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs and dir\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fctori\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[37;28He\u001b[m\u000f starting with a ; ar\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f ignor\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd (comm\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[38;8He\u001b[m\u000f.blacklist_fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fnam\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[40;10He\u001b[m\u000fxclusion of larg\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fs from b\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fing cach\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd. By d\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000ffault all fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[41;5He\u001b[m\u000f cach\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[42;8He\u001b[m\u000f.max_fil\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_siz\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[44;25He\u001b[m\u000fconds) for a sch\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fdul\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fd r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fstart to b\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fgin if th\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f cach\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[45;11He\u001b[m\u000fing acc\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fss\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[46;8He\u001b[m\u000f.forc\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000f_r\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[m\u000fstart_tim\u001b[30m\u001b[103me\u001b[47;159H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f7\u001b[48;3H\u001b[?25h"]
