[0.004, "o", "\u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[14M\u001b[1;48r\u001b[1;6He of the optimized code\u001b[2;8He.save_comme\u001b[4;6Henabled, compilation warnings (including notices and depre\u001b[5;4He recorded and replayed each time a file is included. Otherwise\u001b[6;23He emitted when the file is first cache\u001b[7;8He.re\n\ne \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fistence override (file_\u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fists, etc.) performance feature\u001b[10;8He.enable_file_override\u001b[12;16Here each bit enables or disables the appropriate OPcache\u001b[13;7He\ne.optimization_leve\u001b[16;8He\u001b[18;5He location of the OPcache blacklist file (wildcards allowe\u001b[19;14He blacklist file is a t\u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000ft file that holds the names of file\u001b[20;20He accelerated. The file format is to add each filename\u001b[21;9Hew line. The filename may be a full path or just a file pre\u001b[22;6He., /var/www/x  blacklists all the files and directorie\u001b[23;28He starting with a ; are ignored (comme\u001b[24;8He.blacklist_filename\u001b[26;11H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mx\u001b[m\u000fclusion of large files from being cached. By default all file\u001b[27;5He cache\u001b[28;8He.max_file_size\u001b[30;25Heconds) for a scheduled restart to begin if the cache\u001b[31;11Heing accesse\u001b[32;8He.force_restart_time\r\n\u001b[K\n; OPcache error_log file name. Empty string assumes \"stderr\".\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.error_log=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; All OPcache errors go to the Web server log.\u001b[K\r\n; By default, only fatal errors (level 0) or errors (level 1) are logged.\u001b[K\r\n; You can also enable warnings (level 2), info messages (level 3) or\u001b[K\r\n; debug messages (level 4).\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.log_verbosity_level=1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Preferred Shared Memory back-end. Leave empty and let the system decide.\u001b[K\r\n;opcache.preferred_memory_model=\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; Protect the shared memory from un\u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fpected writing during script \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fecution.\u001b[K\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f56,36        93\u001b[48;4H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.201, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000ft"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[1;2Hopcache.restrict_api=\u001b[7X\r\n\u001b[24X\n; Mapping base of shared memory segments (for Windows only). All the PHP\u001b[4;3Hprocesses have to map shared memory into the same address space. This\u001b[5X\u001b[5;3Hdirective allows to manually fix the \"Unable to reattach to base address\"    \u001b[6;3Herrors.\u001b[53X\nmmap_base=\u001b[7X\u001b[9;3HFacilitates multiple OPcache instances per user (for Windows only). All PHP\u001b[10;2H processes with the same cache ID and user share an OPcache instance.\r\n;opcache.cache_id=\r\n\u001b[71X\u001b[13;3HEnables and sets the second level cache directory.\u001b[14;2H It should improve performance when SHM memory is full, at server restart or\r\n; SHM reset. The default \"\" disables file based caching.\u001b[16;10Hfile_cache=\u001b[18;3HEnables or disables read-only mode for the second level cache directory.\u001b[19;3HIt should improve performance for read-only containers,\u001b[17X\u001b[20;3Hwhen the cache is pre-warmed and packaged alongside the application.   \u001b[21;3HBest used with `opcache.validate_timestamps=0`, `opcache.enable_file_override=1`\u001b[22;3Hand `opcache.file_cache_consistency_checks=0`.\u001b[25X\u001b[23;3HNote: A cache generated with a different build of PHP, a different file path,\u001b[24;2H or different settings (including which \u001b[30m\u001b[103mext\u001b[m\u000fensions are loaded), may be ignored.\r\n;opcache.file_cache_read_only=0\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[27;3HEnables or disables opcode caching in shared memory.\u001b[28;10Hfile_cache_only=0\u001b[30;3HEnables or disables checksum validation when script loaded from file cache.\u001b[31;2Hopcache.file_cache_consistency_checks=1\r\n\u001b[34X\n; Implies opcache.file_cache_only=1 for a certain process that failed to\u001b[34;3Hreattach to the shared memory (for Windows only). Explicitly enabled file\u001b[35;2H cache is required.\r\n;opcache.file_cache_fallback=1\r\n\u001b[46X\u001b[38;3HEnables or disables copying of PHP code (t\u001b[30m\u001b[103mext\u001b[m\u000f segment) into HUGE PAGES\u001b[39;3HUnder certain circumstances (if only a single global PHP process is\u001b[40;3Hstarted from which all others fork), this can increase performance\u001b[41;2H by a tiny amount because TLB misses are reduced.  On the other hand, this\r\n; delays PHP startup, increases memory usage and degrades performance\u001b[43;3Hunder memory pressure - use with care.\u001b[34X\u001b[44;2H Requires appropriate OS configuration.\r\n;opcache.huge_code_pages=0\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f85,42        96\u001b[48;5H\u001b[?25h"]
