[0.005, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[22X\n; When disabled, you must reset the OPcache manually or restart the\u001b[3;3Hwebserver for changes to the filesystem to take effect.\u001b[15X\u001b[4;2Hopcache.validate_timestamps=1\u001b[41X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[6;3HHow often (in seconds) to check file timestamps for changes to the shared\u001b[7;2H memory storage allocation. (\"1\" means validate once per second, but only\r\n; once per request. \"0\" means always validate)\u001b[9;2Hopcache.revalidate_freq=2\u001b[51X\r\n\u001b[70X\u001b[11;2H Enables or disables file search in include_path optimization\r\n;opcache.revalidate_path=0\r\n\u001b[52X\u001b[14;4Hf disabled, all PHPDoc comments are dropped from the code to reduce the   \u001b[15;3Hsize of the optimized code.\u001b[27X\u001b[16;10Hsave_comments=1\u001b[18;3HIf enabled, compilation warnings (including notices and deprecations) will\u001b[19;3Hbe recorded and replayed each time a file is included. Otherwise, compilation\u001b[20;4Harnings will only be emitted when the file is first cached.\u001b[8X\u001b[21;2Hopcache.record_warnings=0\u001b[56X\r\n\u001b[48X\u001b[23;3HAllow file existence override (file_exists, etc.) performance feature.\u001b[7X\u001b[24;2Hopcache.enable_file_override=0\u001b[49X\r\n\u001b[31X\n; A bitmask, where each bit enables or disables the appropriate OPcache\u001b[27;3Hpasses\u001b[46X\u001b[28;10Hoptimization_level=0x7FFFBFFF\u001b[30;2Hopcache.dups_fix=0\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[40X\n; The location of the OPcache blacklist file (wildcards allowed).\u001b[33;3HEach OPcache blacklist file is a text file that holds the names of files\u001b[34;3Hthat should not be accelerated. The file format is to add each filename  \u001b[35;3Hto a new line. The filename may be a full path or just a file prefix\u001b[36;2H (i.e., /var/www/x  blacklists all the files and directories in /var/www\r\n; that start with 'x'). Line starting with a ; are ignored (comments).\u001b[38;2Hopcache.blacklist_filename=\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[69X\u001b[40;3HAllows exclusion of large files from being cached. By default all files\u001b[41;3Hare cached.\u001b[62X\u001b[42;2Hopcache.max_file_size=0\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[40X\u001b[44;3HHow long to wait (in seconds) for a scheduled restart to begin if the cache\u001b[45;2H is not being accessed.  \r\n;opcache.force_restart_timeout=180\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f42,23        92\u001b[48;12H\u001b[?25h"]
