[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H\u001b[96m[exif]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[67X\u001b[2;3HExif UNICODE user comments are handled as UCS-2BE/UCS-2LE and JIS as JIS.\u001b[3;3HWith mbstring support this will automatically be converted into the encoding\r\n; given by corresponding encode setting. When empty mbstring.internal_encoding\r\n; is used. For the decode settings you can distinguish between motorola and\u001b[6;3Hintel byte order. A decode setting must not be empty.\u001b[17X\r\n; https://php.net/exif.encode-unicode\r\n;exif.encode_unicode = ISO-8859-15\r\n\u001b[9X\u001b[10;3Hhttps://php.net/exif.decode-unicode-motorola\u001b[11;2Hexif.decode_unicode_motorola = UCS-2BE\r\n\n; https://php.net/exif.decode-unicode-intel\u001b[14;2Hexif.decode_unicode_intel    = UCS-2LE\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[19X\n; https://php.net/exif.encode-jis\r\n;exif.encode_jis =\r\n\u001b[21X\n; https://php.net/exif.decode-jis-motorola\r\n;exif.decode_jis_motorola = JIS\r\n\u001b[39X\u001b[22;2H https://php.net/exif.decode-jis-intel\r\n;exif.decode_jis_intel    = JIS\r\n\u001b[66X\n\u001b[96m[Tidy]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[15X\r\n; The path to a default tidy configuration file to use when using tidy\u001b[27;3Hhttps://php.net/tidy.default-config    \u001b[28;2Htidy.default_config = /usr/local/lib/php/default.tcfg\u001b[30;3HShould tidy clean and repair output automatically?  \u001b[31;2H WARNING: Do not use this option if you are generating non-html content\r\n; such as dynamic images\u001b[33;3Hhttps://php.net/tidy.clean-output\u001b[30X\r\ntidy.clean_output =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[28X\r\n\u001b[36X\n\u001b[96m[soap]\u001b[37;3H\u001b[m\u000fEnables or disables WSDL caching feature.\u001b[30X\u001b[38;2H https://php.net/soap.wsdl-cache-enabled\r\nsoap.wsdl_cache_enabled=1\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[41;3HSets the directory name where SOAP extension will put cache files.\u001b[7X\u001b[42;3Hhttps://php.net/soap.wsdl-cache-dir\u001b[34X\r\nsoap.wsdl_cache_dir=\u001b[92m\"/tmp\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[25X\r\n\u001b[18X\n; (time to live) Sets the number of second while cached file will be used\u001b[46;3Hinstead of original one.\u001b[41X\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f54,13        87\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.178, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H; https://php.net/mbstring.http-output\u001b[2;2Hmbstring.http_output =\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[4;3Henable automatic encoding translation according to\u001b[26X\u001b[5;3Hmbstring.internal_encoding setting. Input chars are\u001b[22X\u001b[6;3Hconverted to internal encoding by setting this to On\u001b[7;3HNote: Do _not_ use automatic encoding translation for\u001b[8;2H       portable libs/applications.\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.encoding-translation\u001b[10;2Hmbstring.encoding_translation = Off\u001b[10X\r\n\u001b[39X\n; automatic encoding detection order.\u001b[13;3H\"auto\" detect order is changed according to mbstring.language\u001b[14;2H https://php.net/mbstring.detect-order\r\n;mbstring.detect_order = auto\r\n\u001b[33X\u001b[17;2H substitute_character used when character cannot be converted\r\n; one from another\nmbstring.substitute-character\u001b[20;2Hmbstring.substitute_character = none\u001b[22;3HEnable strict encoding detection.    \u001b[23;2Hmbstring.strict_detection = Off\r\n\n; This directive specifies the regex pattern of content types for which mb_output_handler()\u001b[26;3His activated.\u001b[55X\u001b[27;3HDefault: mbstring.http_output_conv_mimetypes=^(text/|application/xhtml\\+xml)\u001b[28;2Hmbstring.http_output_conv_mimetypes=\u001b[17X\u001b[30;3HThis directive specifies maximum stack depth for mbstring regular expressions. It is similar\u001b[31;3Hto the pcre.recursion_limit for PCRE.\u001b[33X\u001b[32;2Hmbstring.regex_stack_limit=100000\r\n\u001b[35X\n; This directive specifies maximum retry count for mbstring regular expressions. It is similar\r\n; to the pcre.backtrack_limit for PCRE.\r\n;mbstring.regex_retry_limit=1000000\r\n\u001b[43X\n\u001b[96m[gd]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[37X\r\n; Tell the jpeg decode to ignore warnings and try to create\r\n; a gd image. The warning will then be displayed as notices\u001b[41;3Hdisabled by default\u001b[47X\u001b[42;19Hgd.jpeg-ignore-warning\r\n;gd.jpeg_ignore_warning = 1\r\n\n\u001b[96m[exif]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[67X\u001b[46;3HExif UNICODE user comments are handled as UCS-2BE/UCS-2LE and JIS as JIS.\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f10,13        85\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.290, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hregister constants casesensitive    \u001b[2;2H https://php.net/com.autoregister-casesensitive\r\n;com.autoregister_casesensitive = false\r\n\u001b[52X\u001b[5;3Hshow warnings on duplicate constant registrations  \u001b[6;3Hhttps://php.net/com.autoregister-verbose\u001b[13X\u001b[7;2Hcom.autoregister_verbose = true\u001b[23X\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[9;3HThe default character set code-page to use when passing strings to and from COM objects.\u001b[10;2H Default: system ANSI code page    \r\n;com.code_page=\r\n\u001b[37X\u001b[13;3HThe version of the .NET framework to use. The value of the setting are the first three parts\u001b[14;3Hof the framework's version number, separated by dots, and prefixed with \"v\", e.g. \"v4.0.30319\".\u001b[15;2Hcom.dotnet_version=\u001b[9X\r\n\n\u001b[96m[mbstring]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[52X\u001b[18;3Hlanguage for internal character representation.\u001b[19;3HThis affects mb_send_mail() and mbstring.detect_order.\u001b[20;2H https://php.net/mbstring.language  \r\n;mbstring.language = Japanese\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[23;2H Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global internal_encoding instead.\r\n; internal/script encoding.\u001b[25;3HSome encoding cannot work as internal encoding. (e.g. SJIS, BIG5, ISO-2022-*)\u001b[12X\u001b[26;3HIf empty, default_charset or internal_encoding or iconv.internal_encoding is used.\u001b[27;3HThe precedence is: default_charset < internal_encoding < iconv.internal_encoding\u001b[28;11Hinternal_encoding =\u001b[8X\u001b[30;3HUse of this INI entry is deprecated, use global input_encoding instead.\u001b[21X\u001b[31;3Hhttp input encoding.\u001b[17X\u001b[32;2H mbstring.encoding_translation = On is needed to use this setting.\r\n; If empty, default_charset or input_encoding or mbstring.input is used.\u001b[34;5He precedence is: default_charset < input_encoding < mbstring.http_input\u001b[19X\u001b[35;3Hhttps://php.net/mbstring.http-input  \u001b[36;11Hhttp_input =\u001b[13X\r\n\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global output_encoding instead.\u001b[39;3Hhttp output encoding.\u001b[36X\u001b[40;3Hmb_output_handler must be registered as output buffer to function.\u001b[41;3HIf empty, default_charset or output_encoding or mbstring.http_output is used.\u001b[42;3HThe precedence is: default_charset < output_encoding < mbstring.http_output\u001b[43;2H To use an output encoding conversion, mbstring's output handler must be set\r\n; otherwise output encoding conversion cannot be performed.\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.http-output\u001b[46;2Hmbstring.http_output =\u001b[52X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f566,13        83\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.196, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3HGiven either in percentages (per-file), or in bytes\u001b[2;3HDefault Value: \"1%\"\u001b[27X\u001b[3;2H Development Value: \"1%\"\u001b[14X\r\n; Production Value: \"1%\"\u001b[5;3Hhttps://php.net/session.upload-progress.freq\u001b[5X\u001b[6;2Hsession.upload_progress.freq =  \"1%\"\u001b[5X\r\n\u001b[32X\n; The minimum delay between updates, in seconds\u001b[9;3HDefault Value: 1\u001b[72X\u001b[10;5Hvelopment Value: 1\u001b[10X\u001b[11;2H Production Value: 1\r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.min-freq\u001b[13;2Hsession.upload_progress.min_freq = \"1\"\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[97X\u001b[15;2H Only write session data when session data is changed. Enabled by default.\r\n; https://php.net/session.lazy-write\r\n;session.lazy_write = On\r\n\u001b[49X\n\u001b[96m[Assertion]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[45X\u001b[20;3HSwitch whether to compile assertions at all (to have no overhead at run-time)\u001b[21;2H -1: Do not compile at all  \r\n;  0: Jump over assertion at run-time\u001b[23;3H 1: Execute assertions\u001b[52X\u001b[24;3HChanging from or to a negative value is only possible in php.ini!\u001b[25;3H(For turning assertions on and off at run-time, toggle zend.assertions between the values 1 and 0)\u001b[26;3HDefault Value: 1\u001b[66X\u001b[27;3HDevelopment Value: 1\u001b[60X\u001b[28;2H Production Value: -1\u001b[7X\r\n; https://php.net/zend.assertions\r\nzend.assertions =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[22X\n\u001b[96m[COM]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[62X\u001b[33;3Hpath to a file containing GUIDs, IIDs or filenames of files with TypeLibs\u001b[34;3Hhttps://php.net/com.typelib-file\u001b[41X\u001b[35;2Hcom.typelib_file =\u001b[18X\r\n\u001b[22X\n; allow Distributed-COM calls\u001b[38;3Hhttps://php.net/com.allow-dcom\u001b[42X\u001b[39;2Hcom.allow_dcom = true \r\n\u001b[68X\u001b[41;3Hautoregister constants of a component's typelib on com_load()\u001b[16X\u001b[42;3Hhttps://php.net/com.autoregister-typelib\u001b[35X\u001b[43;2Hcom.autoregister_typelib = true\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[59X\u001b[45;3Hregister constants casesensitive    \u001b[46;2H https://php.net/com.autoregister-casesensitive\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f22,13        80\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.194, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3HURL rewriter does not rewrite absolute URLs by default.\u001b[2;3HTo enable rewrites for absolute paths, target hosts must be specified\u001b[3;3Hat RUNTIME. i.e. use ini_set()\u001b[4;3H<form> tags is special. PHP will check action attribute's URL regardless\u001b[5;3Hof session.trans_sid_tags setting.\u001b[10X\u001b[6;2H If no host is defined, HTTP_HOST will be used for allowed host.\r\n; Example value: php.net,www.php.net,wiki.php.net\u001b[8;3HUse \",\" for multiple hosts. No spaces are allowed.\u001b[9;18H\"\"\u001b[10;22H\"\"\u001b[11;21H\"\"\u001b[12;2Hsession.trans_sid_hosts=\"\"\u001b[23X\r\n\u001b[39X\n; Enable upload progress tracking in $_SESSION\u001b[15;3HDefault Value: On\u001b[56X\u001b[16;3HDevelopment Value: On\u001b[13X\u001b[17;2H Production Value: On  \r\n; https://php.net/session.upload-progress.enabled\r\n;session.upload_progress.enabled = On\r\n\u001b[79X\u001b[21;3HCleanup the progress information as soon as all POST data has been read\u001b[22;3H(i.e. upload completed).\u001b[11X\u001b[23;3HDefault Value: On\u001b[5X\u001b[24;3HDevelopment Value: On\u001b[44X\u001b[25;3HProduction Value: On\u001b[78X\u001b[26;3Hhttps://php.net/session.upload-progress.cleanup\u001b[27;2Hsession.upload_progress.cleanup = On\r\n\u001b[22X\u001b[29;3HA prefix used for the upload progress key in $_SESSION\r\n; Default Value: \"upload_progress_\"\r\n; Development Value: \"upload_progress_\"\r\n; Production Value: \"upload_progress_\"\u001b[33;3Hhttps://php.net/session.upload-progress.prefix\u001b[27X\u001b[34;2Hsession.upload_progress.prefix = \"upload_progress_\"\r\n\u001b[19X\n; The index name (concatenated with the prefix) in $_SESSION\u001b[37;3Hcontaining the upload progress information\u001b[38;3HDefault Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[39;2H Development Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\r\n; Production Value: \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\u001b[41;3Hhttps://php.net/session.upload-progress.name\u001b[17X\u001b[42;2Hsession.upload_progress.name = \"PHP_SESSION_UPLOAD_PROGRESS\"\r\n\u001b[32X\n; How frequently the upload progress should be updated.\u001b[45;3HGiven either in percentages (per-file), or in bytes\u001b[46;3HDefault Value: \"1%\"\u001b[27X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f478,13        78\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.172, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3H      collection through a shell script, cron entry, or some other method.\u001b[2;3H      For example, the following script is the equivalent of setting \u001b[3;3H      session.gc_maxlifetime to 1440 (1440 seconds = 24 minutes):\u001b[4;3H         find /path/to/sessions -cmin +24 -type f | xargs rm\u001b[12X\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[6;3HCheck HTTP Referer to invalidate externally stored URLs containing ids.\u001b[7;3HHTTP_REFERER has to contain this substring for the session to be\u001b[8;3Hconsidered as valid.\u001b[30X\u001b[9;3Hhttps://php.net/session.referer-check\r\nsession.referer_check =\r\n\u001b[22X\u001b[12;2H Set to {nocache,private,public,} to determine HTTP caching aspects\r\n; or leave this empty to avoid sending anti-caching headers.\u001b[14;3Hhttps://php.net/session.cache-limiter\u001b[7X\r\nsession.cache_limiter =\u001b[92m nocache\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[23X\u001b[17;3HDocument expires after n minutes.\u001b[18;27Hcache-expire\u001b[11X\r\nsession.cache_expire = 180\u001b[11X\u001b[21;3Htrans sid support is disabled by default.\u001b[30X\u001b[22;3HUse of trans sid may risk your users' security.\u001b[23;3HUse this option with caution.\u001b[24;3H- User may send URL contains active session ID\u001b[25;3H  to other person via. email/irc/etc.\u001b[26;3H- URL that contains active session ID may be stored\u001b[27;2H   in publicly accessible computer. \r\n; - User may access your site with the same session ID\u001b[29;3H  always using URL stored in browser's history or bookmarks.\u001b[30;3Hhttps://php.net/session.use-trans-sid\r\nsession.use_trans_sid = 0\u001b[14X\r\n\u001b[38X\u001b[33;3HThe URL rewriter will look for URLs in a defined set of HTML tags.\u001b[34;2H <form> is special; if you include them here, the rewriter will\r\n; add a hidden <input> field with the info which is otherwise appended\u001b[36;3Hto URLs. <form> tag's action attribute URL will not be modified\u001b[37;3Hunless it is specified.\u001b[19X\u001b[38;3HNote that all valid entries require a \"=\", even if no value follows.\u001b[39;5Hfault Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[40;3HDevelopment Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[41;3HProduction Value: \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[42;2H https://php.net/url-rewriter.tags\u001b[26X\r\nsession.trans_sid_tags =\u001b[92m \"a=href,area=href,frame=src,form=\"\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[55X\u001b[45;3HURL rewriter does not rewrite absolute URLs by default.\u001b[46;3HTo enable rewrites for absolute paths, target hosts must be specified\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f34,13        75\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.311, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[Hsession.cookie_domain =\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[70X\u001b[3;3HWhether or not to add the httpOnly flag to the cookie, which makes it\u001b[4;3Hinaccessible to browser scripting languages such as JavaScript.\r\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-httponly\r\nsession.cookie_httponly =\u001b[48X\r\n\u001b[66X\u001b[8;3HAdd SameSite attribute to cookie to help mitigate Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF/XSRF)\u001b[9;3HCurrent valid values are \"Strict\", \"Lax\" or \"None\". When using \"None\",\r\n; make sure to include the quotes, as `none` is interpreted like `false` in ini files.\r\n; https://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-west-first-party-cookies-07\r\nsession.cookie_samesite =\u001b[43X\r\n\u001b[60X\u001b[14;3HHandler used to serialize data. php is the standard serializer of PHP.\r\n; https://php.net/session.serialize-handler\r\nsession.serialize_handler =\u001b[92m php\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[18;3HDefines the probability that the 'garbage collection' process is started on every\r\n; session initialization. The probability is calculated by using gc_probability/gc_divisor,\r\n; e.g. 1/100 means there is a 1% chance that the GC process starts on each request.\u001b[21;3HDefault Value: 1\u001b[25X\u001b[22;3HDevelopment Value: 1\u001b[27X\u001b[23;3HProduction Value: 1\u001b[10X\u001b[24;3Hhttps://php.net/session.gc-probability\u001b[8X\r\nsession.gc_probability = 1\u001b[13X\r\n\u001b[53X\u001b[27;3HDefines the probability that the 'garbage collection' process is started on every\u001b[28;3Hsession initialization. The probability is calculated by using gc_probability/gc_divisor,\u001b[29;3He.g. 1/100 means there is a 1% chance that the GC process starts on each request.\u001b[30;3HFor high volume production servers, using a value of 1000 is a more efficient approach.\r\n; Default Value: 100\u001b[5X\r\n; Development Value: 1000\u001b[33;3HProduction Value: 1000\u001b[44X\u001b[34;3Hhttps://php.net/session.gc-divisor\u001b[28X\r\nsession.gc_divisor = 1000\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[65X\u001b[37;3HAfter this number of seconds, stored data will be seen as 'garbage' and\u001b[38;3Hcleaned up by the garbage collection process.\u001b[23X\u001b[39;3Hhttps://php.net/session.gc-maxlifetime\u001b[11X\r\nsession.gc_maxlifetime = 1440\u001b[26X\r\n\u001b[54X\u001b[42;3HNOTE: If you are using the subdirectory option for storing session files\r\n;       (see session.save_path above), then garbage collection does *not*\r\n;       happen automatically.  You will need to do your own garbage\u001b[45;3H      collection through a shell script, cron entry, or some other method.\u001b[46;3H      For example, the following script is the equivalent of setting \u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f390,13        73\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.244, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H; Whether to use strict session mode.\r\n; Strict session mode does not accept an uninitialized session ID, and\u001b[3;3Hregenerates the session ID if the browser sends an uninitialized session ID.\u001b[4;3HStrict mode protects applications from session fixation via a session adoption\u001b[5;3Hvulnerability. It is disabled by default for maximum compatibility, but\r\n; enabling it is encouraged.\r\n; https://wiki.php.net/rfc/strict_sessions\r\nsession.use_strict_mode = 0\u001b[63X\r\n\u001b[72X\u001b[10;3HWhether to use cookies.\u001b[61X\u001b[11;11Hphp.net/session.use-cookies\u001b[26X\u001b[12;9Huse_cookies = 1  \u001b[14;3Hhttps://php.net/session.cookie-secure\u001b[33X\u001b[15;2Hsession.cookie_secure =\u001b[19X\r\n\u001b[31X\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-partitioned\u001b[18;2Hsession.cookie_partitioned = 0\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[91X\u001b[20;3HThis option forces PHP to fetch and use a cookie for storing and maintaining\u001b[5X\u001b[21;3Hthe session id. We encourage this operation as it's very helpful in combating\u001b[22;3Hsession hijacking when not specifying and managing your own session id. It is\u001b[23;3Hnot the be-all and end-all of session hijacking defense, but it's a good start.\u001b[24;27Huse-only-cookies\u001b[25;9Huse_only_cookies = 1\u001b[27;3HName of the session (used as cookie name).\u001b[39X\u001b[28;3Hhttps://php.net/session.name\u001b[61X\r\nsession.name =\u001b[92m PHPSESSID\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[59X\r\n\u001b[89X\u001b[31;3HInitialize session on request startup.\u001b[32;3Hhttps://php.net/session.auto-start\r\nsession.auto_start = 0  \r\n\u001b[36X\n; Lifetime in seconds of cookie or, if 0, until browser is restarted.\r\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-lifetime\r\nsession.cookie_lifetime = 0\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[47X\u001b[39;3HThe path for which the cookie is valid.\r\n; https://php.net/session.cookie-path\r\nsession.cookie_path =\u001b[92m /\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[74X\u001b[43;3HThe domain for which the cookie is valid.\u001b[30X\u001b[44;3Hhttps://php.net/session.cookie-domain\u001b[28X\r\nsession.cookie_domain =\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[70X\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f46,0-1       71\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\r\u001b[A\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H\u001b[37X\n\u001b[96m[bcmath]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[62X\u001b[3;3HNumber of decimal digits for all bcmath functions.\u001b[26X\u001b[4;3Hhttps://php.net/bcmath.scale\u001b[50X\r\nbcmath.scale = 0\u001b[57X\r\n\u001b[28X\n\u001b[96m[browscap]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[32X\r\n; https://php.net/browscap \r\n;browscap = extra/browscap.ini\r\n\u001b[25X\n\u001b[96m[Session]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[28X\r\n; Handler used to store/retrieve data.\r\n; https://php.net/session.save-handler\r\nsession.save_handler =\u001b[92m files\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[11X\r\n\u001b[24X\n; Argument passed to save_handler.  In the case of files, this is the path\u001b[17;3Hwhere data files are stored. Note: Windows users have to change this\u001b[18;2H variable in order to use PHP's session functions.\r\n;\u001b[20;5He path can be defined as:\u001b[49X\u001b[21;2H\u001b[78X\u001b[22;3H    session.save_path = \"N;/path\"\u001b[44X\u001b[23;2H\u001b[80X\u001b[24;3Hwhere N is an integer.  Instead of storing all the session files in\r\n; /path, what this will do is use subdirectories N-levels deep, and\r\n; store the session data in those directories.  This is useful if\u001b[27;3Hyour OS has problems with many files in one directory, and is\u001b[28;3Ha more efficient layout for servers that handle many sessions.\r\n;\u001b[23X\r\n; NOTE 1: PHP will not create this directory structure automatically.\u001b[31;3H        You can use the script in the ext/session dir for that purpose.\u001b[32;3HNOTE 2: See the section on garbage collection below if you choose to\r\n;         use subdirectories for session storage\r\n;\u001b[35;3HThe file storage module creates files using mode 600 by default.   \u001b[36;3HYou can change that by using\u001b[11X\r\n;\u001b[26X\r\n;     session.save_path = \"N;MODE;/path\"\u001b[39;2H\u001b[40X\u001b[40;3Hwhere MODE is the octal representation of the mode. Note that this\r\n; does not overwrite the process's umask.\r\n; https://php.net/session.save-path\u001b[43;2Hsession.save_path = \"/tmp\"\u001b[16X\r\n\u001b[39X\n; Whether to use strict session mode.\r\n; Strict session mode does not accept an uninitialized session ID, and\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f02,13        68\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H; Default size of the mysqlnd memory pool, which is used by result sets.\r\n;mysqlnd.mempool_default_size = 16000\r\n\u001b[52X\u001b[4;3HSize of a pre-allocated buffer used when sending commands to MySQL in bytes.\r\n;mysqlnd.net_cmd_buffer_size = 2048\r\n\n; Size of a pre-allocated buffer used for reading data sent by the server in\u001b[8;3Hbytes.\u001b[18X\u001b[9;2Hmysqlnd.net_read_buffer_size = 32768\r\n\n; Timeout for network requests in seconds.\u001b[12;2Hmysqlnd.net_read_timeout = 31536000  \r\n\u001b[38X\n; SHA-256 Authentication Plugin related. File with the MySQL server public RSA\r\n; key.\u001b[16;2Hmysqlnd.sha256_server_public_key =\u001b[39X\r\n\u001b[70X\n\u001b[96m[PostgreSQL]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[39X\u001b[19;2H Allow or prevent persistent links.\u001b[20;3Hhttps://php.net/pgsql.allow-persistent\r\npgsql.allow_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[23;2H Detect broken persistent links always with pg_pconnect().\u001b[24;3HAuto reset feature requires a little overheads.\u001b[20X\u001b[25;3Hhttps://php.net/pgsql.auto-reset-persistent\u001b[22X\r\npgsql.auto_reset_persistent =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[32X\r\n\u001b[63X\u001b[28;3HMaximum number of persistent links.  -1 means no limit.\u001b[7X\u001b[29;2H https://php.net/pgsql.max-persistent\r\npgsql.max_persistent =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[44X\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[32;3HMaximum number of links (persistent+non persistent).  -1 means no limit.\u001b[33;3Hhttps://php.net/pgsql.max-links\u001b[15X\r\npgsql.max_links =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[66X\u001b[36;3HIgnore PostgreSQL backends Notice message or not.\u001b[37;2H Notice message logging require a little overheads.\u001b[38;3Hhttps://php.net/pgsql.ignore-notice   \r\npgsql.ignore_notice = 0\r\n\u001b[68X\u001b[41;3HLog PostgreSQL backends Notice message or not.\u001b[42;3HUnless pgsql.ignore_notice=0, module cannot log notice message.\u001b[43;2H https://php.net/pgsql.log-notice\r\npgsql.log_notice = 0\r\n\u001b[37X\n\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m[\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96mbcmath\u001b[0;10;4;1m\u000f\u001b[96m]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[62X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f258,8         66\u001b[46;8H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;8H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hhttps://php.net/mysqli.default-socket\u001b[33X\r\nmysqli.default_socket =\u001b[14X\u001b[4;3HDefault host for mysqli_connect().\u001b[42X\u001b[5;2H https://php.net/mysqli.default-host\r\nmysqli.default_host =\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[8;3HDefault user for mysqli_connect().\u001b[9;2H https://php.net/mysqli.default-user\r\nmysqli.default_user =\r\n\u001b[42X\u001b[12;2H Default password for mysqli_connect().\r\n; Note that this is generally a *bad* idea to store passwords in this file.\u001b[14;3H*Any* user with PHP access can run 'echo get_cfg_var(\"mysqli.default_pw\")   \u001b[15;3Hand reveal this password!  And of course, any users with read access to this\u001b[16;2H file will be able to reveal the password as well.\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.default-pw\r\nmysqli.default_pw =\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[20;3HIf this option is enabled, closing a persistent connection will rollback\r\n; any pending transactions of this connection, before it is put back\r\n; into the persistent connection pool.\u001b[23;2Hmysqli.rollback_on_cached_plink = Off\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[49X\n\u001b[96m[mysqlnd]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[36X\r\n; Enable / Disable collection of general statistics by mysqlnd which can be\r\n; used to tune and monitor MySQL operations.\r\nmysqlnd.collect_statistics =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[26X\r\n\u001b[38X\n; Enable / Disable collection of memory usage statistics by mysqlnd which can be\r\n; used to tune and monitor MySQL operations.\u001b[32;3HDefault Value: Off\u001b[54X\u001b[33;3HDevelopment Value: On\u001b[10X\r\n; Production Value: Off\r\nmysqlnd.collect_memory_statistics =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[51X\u001b[37;3HRecords communication from all extensions using mysqlnd to the specified log\u001b[38;3Hfile.\u001b[30X\r\n; https://php.net/mysqlnd.debug\r\n;mysqlnd.debug =\r\n\u001b[48X\u001b[42;3HDefines which queries will be logged.\u001b[26X\u001b[43;2Hmysqlnd.log_mask = 0\u001b[13X\r\n\u001b[20X\n; Default size of the mysqlnd memory pool, which is used by result sets.\r\n;mysqlnd.mempool_default_size = 16000\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f14,13        63\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H\u001b[39X\n; Maximum number of links (persistent + non-persistent).  -1 means no limit.\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.max-links\r\nodbc.max_links =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[17X\r\n\u001b[37X\n; Handling of LONG fields.  Returns number of bytes to variables.  0 means\r\n; passthru.\u001b[8;3Hhttps://php.net/odbc.defaultlrl   \r\nodbc.defaultlrl = 4096\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[21X\n; Handling of binary data.  0 means passthru, 1 return as is, 2 convert to char.\u001b[12;3HSee the documentation on odbc_binmode and odbc_longreadlen for an explanation\u001b[13;3Hof odbc.defaultlrl and odbc.defaultbinmode\u001b[31X\u001b[14;3Hhttps://php.net/odbc.defaultbinmode\u001b[38X\r\nodbc.defaultbinmode = 1\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[51X\n\u001b[96m[MySQLi]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[27X\r\n\u001b[19X\n; Maximum number of persistent links.  -1 means no limit.\u001b[20;3Hhttps://php.net/mysqli.max-persistent\u001b[35X\r\nmysqli.max_persistent =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[42X\r\n\u001b[38X\u001b[23;2H Allow accessing, from PHP's perspective, local files with LOAD DATA statements\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.allow_local_infile\r\n;mysqli.allow_local_infile = On\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[27;3HIt allows the user to specify a folder where files that can be sent via LOAD DATA\r\n; LOCAL can exist. It is ignored if mysqli.allow_local_infile is enabled.\r\n;mysqli.local_infile_directory =\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[31;3HAllow or prevent persistent links.\u001b[8X\u001b[32;3Hhttps://php.net/mysqli.allow-persistent\r\nmysqli.allow_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[23X\n; Maximum number of links.  -1 means no limit.\r\n; https://php.net/mysqli.max-links\r\nmysqli.max_links =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[57X\r\n\u001b[7X\u001b[39;3HDefault port number for mysqli_connect().\u001b[40;2H https://php.net/mysqli.default-port\r\nmysqli.default_port = 3306\r\n\u001b[39X\u001b[43;2H Default socket name for local MySQL connects.  If empty, uses the built-in\r\n; MySQL defaults.\u001b[45;3Hhttps://php.net/mysqli.default-socket\u001b[33X\r\nmysqli.default_socket =\u001b[14X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f170,13        61\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[2;3HUse mixed LF and CRLF line separators to keep compatibility with some\u001b[5X\u001b[3;3HRFC 2822 non conformant MTA.  \r\nmail.mixed_lf_and_crlf =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[6;3H\u001b[m\u000fControl line ending mode for mail messages and headers.\u001b[17X\u001b[7;3HPossible values: \"crlf\" (default), \"lf\", \"mixed\", \"os\"\u001b[8;3H- crlf: Use CRLF line endings  \r\n; - lf: Use LF line endings only (converts CRLF in message to LF)\r\n; - mixed: Same as mail.mixed_lf_and_crlf = On\u001b[11;3H- os: Use CRLF on Windows, LF on other systems\u001b[32X\r\nmail.cr_lf_mode =\u001b[92m crlf\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[57X\r\n\u001b[44X\u001b[14;3HThe path to a log file that will log all mail() calls. Log entries include\r\n; the full path of the script, line number, To address and headers.\r\n;mail.log =\r\n; Log mail to syslog (Event Log on Windows).\r\n;mail.log = syslog\r\n\u001b[57X\n\u001b[96m[ODBC]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[33X\r\n; https://php.net/odbc.default-db\r\n;odbc.default_db    =  Not yet implemented\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[24;19Hodbc.default-user\u001b[8X\u001b[25;2Hodbc.default_user  =  Not yet implemented\u001b[27;3Hhttps://php.net/odbc.default-pw\u001b[50X\u001b[28;2Hodbc.default_pw    =  Not yet implemented\u001b[31X\r\n\u001b[32X\n; Controls the ODBC cursor model.\u001b[31;3HDefault: SQL_CURSOR_STATIC (default).\u001b[32;2Hodbc.default_cursortype\u001b[17X\r\n\u001b[28X\n; Allow or prevent persistent links.\u001b[35;3Hhttps://php.net/odbc.allow-persistent\u001b[7X\r\nodbc.allow_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[8X\r\n\u001b[21X\n; Check that a connection is still valid before reuse.\u001b[39;3Hhttps://php.net/odbc.check-persistent    \r\nodbc.check_persistent =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[11X\r\n\u001b[26X\n; Maximum number of persistent links.  -1 means no limit.\u001b[43;3Hhttps://php.net/odbc.max-persistent\u001b[39X\r\nodbc.max_persistent =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[39X\n; Maximum number of links (persistent + non-persistent).  -1 means no limit.\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f26,13        59\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.030, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H; library to be compiled with JIT support.\u001b[2;2Hpcre.jit=1\u001b[60X\r\n\u001b[30X\n\u001b[96m[Pdo]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[23X\r\n; Whether to pool ODBC connections. Can be one of \"strict\", \"relaxed\" or \"off\"\u001b[6;3Hhttps://php.net/pdo-odbc.connection-pooling\u001b[12X\u001b[7;2Hpdo_odbc.connection_pooling=strict\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[31X\n\u001b[96m[Pdo_mysql]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[54X\u001b[10;3HDefault socket name for local MySQL connects.  If empty, uses the built-in\u001b[11;3HMySQL defaults.\u001b[31X\r\npdo_mysql.default_socket=\r\n\n\u001b[96m[Phar]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[70X\u001b[15;3Hhttps://php.net/phar.readonly\u001b[36X\u001b[16;2Hphar.readonly = On\r\n\u001b[44X\u001b[18;2H https://php.net/phar.require-hash\r\n;phar.require_hash = On\r\n\u001b[6X\u001b[21;2Hphar.cache_list =\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[42X\n\u001b[96m[mail function]\u001b[24;3H\u001b[m\u000fFor Win32 only.\u001b[18X\u001b[25;2H https://php.net/smtp\u001b[20X\r\nSMTP =\u001b[92m localhost\u001b[27;19H\u001b[m\u000fsmtp-port\u001b[6X\r\nsmtp_port = 25\u001b[28X\u001b[30;3HFor Win32 only.\u001b[16X\u001b[31;3Hhttps://php.net/sendmail-from\u001b[8X\u001b[32;2Hsendmail_from = me@example.com\u001b[34;3HFor Unix only.  You may supply arguments as well (default: \"sendmail -t -i\").\u001b[35;19Hsendmail-path\u001b[8X\r\n;sendmail_path =\u001b[10X\u001b[38;3HForce the addition of the specified parameters to be passed as extra parameters\u001b[39;3Hto the sendmail binary. These parameters will always replace the value of\r\n; the 5th parameter to mail().\r\n;mail.force_extra_parameters =\r\n\u001b[57X\u001b[43;3HAdd X-PHP-Originating-Script: that will include uid of the script followed by the filename\r\nmail.add_x_header =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[46;3HUse mixed LF and CRLF line separators to keep compatibility with some\u001b[5X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f082,13        56\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.030, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3HThe precedence is: default_charset < output_encoding < iconv.output_encoding\u001b[2;2H To use an output encoding conversion, iconv's output handler must be set\r\n; otherwise output encoding conversion cannot be performed.\r\n;iconv.output_encoding =\r\n\u001b[78X\n\u001b[96m[intl]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[39X\u001b[7;2Hintl.default_locale =\u001b[13X\r\n; This directive allows you to produce PHP errors when some error\r\n; happens within intl functions. The value is the level of the error produced.\u001b[10;11His 0, which does not produce any errors.\u001b[26X\u001b[11;3HThis directive is deprecated.\r\n;intl.error_level = E_WARNING\r\n; If enabled this directive indicates that when an error occurs within an\r\n; intl function a IntlException should be thrown.\u001b[15;3HDefault is Off, which means errors need to be handled manually.\u001b[16;2Hintl.use_exceptions = On\r\n\n\u001b[96m[sqlite3]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[26X\u001b[19;2H Directory pointing to SQLite3 extensions\r\n; https://php.net/sqlite3.extension-dir\u001b[21;2Hsqlite3.extension_dir =\r\n\n; SQLite defensive mode flag (only available from SQLite 3.26+)\u001b[24;3HWhen the defensive flag is enabled, language features that allow ordinary\u001b[25;3HSQL to deliberately corrupt the database file are disabled. This forbids\r\n; writing directly to the schema, shadow tables (eg. FTS data tables), or\u001b[27;3Hthe sqlite_dbpage virtual table.\r\n; https://www.sqlite.org/c3ref/c_dbconfig_defensive.html\r\n; (for older SQLite versions, this flag has no use)\u001b[30;2Hsqlite3.defensive = 1\r\n\u001b[31X\n\u001b[96m[Pcre]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[25X\r\n; PCRE library backtracking limit.\u001b[34;3Hhttps://php.net/pcre.backtrack-limit\u001b[41X\u001b[35;2Hpcre.backtrack_limit=100000   \r\n\u001b[16X\n; PCRE library recursion limit.\u001b[38;3HPlease note that if you set this value to a high number you may consume all    \u001b[39;4Hhe available process stack and eventually crash PHP (due to reaching the\u001b[40;3Hstack size limit imposed by the Operating System).\u001b[41;2H https://php.net/pcre.recursion-limit\r\n;pcre.recursion_limit=100000\r\n\u001b[92X\n; Enables or disables JIT compilation of patterns. This requires the PCRE\r\n; library to be compiled with JIT support.\u001b[46;2Hpcre.jit=1\u001b[60X\u001b[47;155H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f38,11        54\u001b[46;11H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;11H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3HModule Settings ;\u001b[59X\u001b[2;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[59X\n\u001b[96m[CLI Server]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[12X\r\n; Whether the CLI web server uses ANSI color coding in its terminal output.\r\ncli_server.color =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[22X\n\u001b[96m[Date]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[59X\u001b[9;3HDefines the default timezone used by the date functions\u001b[21X\u001b[10;3Hhttps://php.net/date.timezone\u001b[19X\u001b[11;2Hdate.timezone =\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[29X\u001b[13;3Hhttps://php.net/date.default-latitude\u001b[34X\u001b[14;2Hdate.default_latitude = 31.7667\u001b[17X\r\n\u001b[65X\u001b[16;2H https://php.net/date.default-longitude\r\n;date.default_longitude = 35.2333\r\n\u001b[9X\u001b[19;3Hhttps://php.net/date.sunrise-zenith\u001b[5X\u001b[20;2Hdate.sunrise_zenith = 90.833333\u001b[7X\r\n\u001b[24X\n; https://php.net/date.sunset-zenith\u001b[23;2Hdate.sunset_zenith = 90.833333\u001b[32X\r\n\u001b[75X\n\u001b[96m[filter]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[66X\u001b[26;3Hhttps://php.net/filter.default\u001b[41X\u001b[27;2Hfilter.default = unsafe_raw\u001b[6X\r\n\u001b[56X\u001b[29;3Hhttps://php.net/filter.default-flags\u001b[13X\u001b[30;2Hfilter.default_flags =\u001b[32;2H\u001b[96miconv]\u001b[33;3H\u001b[m\u000fUse of this INI entry is deprecated, use global input_encoding instead.\u001b[34;3HIf empty, default_charset or input_encoding or iconv.input_encoding is used.\u001b[35;2H The precedence is: default_charset < input_encoding < iconv.input_encoding\r\n;iconv.input_encoding =\r\n\u001b[31X\u001b[38;3HUse of this INI entry is deprecated, use global internal_encoding instead. \u001b[39;3HIf empty, default_charset or internal_encoding or iconv.internal_encoding is used.\u001b[40;3HThe precedence is: default_charset < internal_encoding < iconv.internal_encoding\u001b[41;2Hiconv.internal_encoding =\u001b[12X\r\n\u001b[28X\n; Use of this INI entry is deprecated, use global output_encoding instead.\u001b[44;3HIf empty, default_charset or output_encoding or iconv.output_encoding is used.\u001b[45;3HThe precedence is: default_charset < output_encoding < iconv.output_encoding\u001b[46;2H To use an output encoding conversion, iconv's output handler must be set\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f994,13         51\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3H  extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[2;2H\u001b[18X\r\n; Note : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('extension=<ext>.so' and\r\n; 'extension='php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\u001b[5;3Hdeprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\r\n; move to the new ('extension=<ext>) syntax.\r\n;\r\n;extension=bcmath\u001b[9;2Hextension=bz2\u001b[43X\u001b[10;2Hextension=calendar\u001b[12X\r\nextension=\u001b[92mcurl\u001b[m\u000f  \r\n;extension=dba\u001b[13;2Hextension=enchant\u001b[21X\u001b[14;2Hextension=exif\u001b[17X\r\n;extension=ffi\u001b[16;2Hextension=ftp\u001b[26X\u001b[17;2Hextension=gd\u001b[20X\r\n;extension=gettext\u001b[19;2Hextension=gmp\u001b[23X\u001b[20;2Hextension=iconv\u001b[16X\r\n;extension=intl\u001b[22;2Hextension=ldap\u001b[21X\u001b[23;2Hextension=mysqli\u001b[14X\r\n;extension=odbc\r\n;extension=pdo_dblib\u001b[26;2Hextension=pdo_mysql\u001b[12X\u001b[27;2Hextension=pdo_odbc\u001b[9X\r\n;extension=pdo_pgsql\u001b[29;2Hextension=pdo_sqlite\u001b[17X\u001b[30;2Hextension=pgsql\u001b[7X\r\n;extension=shmop\r\n;extension=snmp\u001b[33;2Hextension=soap\u001b[58X\u001b[34;2Hextension=sockets\u001b[60X\u001b[35;2Hextension=sodium\u001b[59X\u001b[36;2Hextension=sqlite3\u001b[5X\r\n;extension=sysvmsg\u001b[38;2Hextension=sysvsem\u001b[58X\u001b[39;2Hextension=sysvshm\u001b[66X\u001b[40;2Hextension=tidy\u001b[67X\u001b[41;2Hextension=xsl\u001b[12X\r\nextension=\u001b[92mzip\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[74X\u001b[44;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[61X\u001b[45;3HModule Settings ;\u001b[59X\u001b[46;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[55X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f50,13         49\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.030, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hhttps://php.net/allow-url-fopen\u001b[9X\r\nallow_url_fopen =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[4;3HWhether to allow include/require to open URLs (like https:// or ftp://) as files.\u001b[5;3Hhttps://php.net/allow-url-include\u001b[40X\r\nallow_url_include =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[21X\r\n \n Define the anonymous ftp password (your email address). PHP's default setting\u001b[9;2H for this is empty.\u001b[10;2H https://php.net/from\r\n;from=\"john@doe.com\"\r\n\u001b[14X\u001b[13;2H Define the User-Agent string. PHP's default setting for this is empty.\u001b[14;2H https://php.net/user-agent\u001b[15;2Huser_agent=\"PHP\"\r\n\u001b[14X\u001b[17;2H Default timeout for socket based streams (seconds)\u001b[18;2H https://php.net/default-socket-timeout\r\ndefault_socket_timeout = 60\r\n\u001b[16X\u001b[21;2H If your scripts have to deal with files from Macintosh systems,\u001b[22;2H or you are running on a Mac and need to deal with files from\u001b[23;2H unix or win32 systems, setting this flag will cause PHP to\u001b[24;2H automatically detect the EOL character in those files so that\u001b[25;2H fgets() and file() will work regardless of the source of the file.\u001b[26;2H https://php.net/auto-detect-line-endings\u001b[27;2Hauto_detect_line_endings = Off\r\n\u001b[20X\u001b[29;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[30;2H Dynamic Extensions ;\u001b[31;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[33;2H If you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\u001b[34;2H syntax:\u001b[9X\u001b[35;2H\u001b[16X\n   extension=modulename\u001b[37;2H\u001b[17X\n For example:    \u001b[39;2H\u001b[17X\n   extension=mysqli\u001b[41;2H\u001b[13X\r\n; When the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\r\n; directory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[44;2H\u001b[18X\u001b[45;3H  extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[46;2H\u001b[18X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f06,1          47\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\r\u001b[A\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3HDisable logging through FastCGI connection. PHP's default behavior is to enable\r\n; this feature.\u001b[5X\r\n;fastcgi.logging = 0\r\n\u001b[83X\u001b[5;3Hcgi.rfc2616_headers configuration option tells PHP what type of headers to\r\n; use when sending HTTP response code. If set to 0, PHP sends Status: header that\r\n; is supported by Apache. When this option is set to 1, PHP will send\u001b[8;3HRFC2616 compliant header.\u001b[52X\u001b[9;3HDefault is zero.  \u001b[10;19Hcgi.rfc2616-headers\u001b[11;2Hcgi.rfc2616_headers = 0\u001b[13;3Hcgi.check_shebang_line controls whether CGI PHP checks for line starting with #!\u001b[14;3H(shebang) at the top of the running script. This line might be needed if the\u001b[15;2H script support running both as stand-alone script and via PHP CGI<. PHP in CGI\r\n; mode skips this line and ignores its content if this directive is turned on.\u001b[17;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.check-shebang-line\u001b[12X\u001b[18;2Hcgi.check_shebang_line=1\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[27X\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[21;3HFile Uploads ;\u001b[49X\u001b[22;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[60X\u001b[24;3HWhether to allow HTTP file uploads.\u001b[26X\u001b[25;3Hhttps://php.net/file-uploads\u001b[38X\r\nfile_uploads =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[25X\r\n\u001b[31X\n; Temporary directory for HTTP uploaded files (will use system default if not\u001b[29;2H specified).\u001b[9X\u001b[30;3Hhttps://php.net/upload-tmp-dir\u001b[31;2Hupload_tmp_dir =\u001b[5X\u001b[33;3HMaximum allowed size for uploaded files.\u001b[32X\u001b[34;3Hhttps://php.net/upload-max-filesize\r\nupload_max_filesize =\u001b[92m 2M\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[24X\u001b[37;2H Maximum number of files that can be uploaded via a single request\r\nmax_file_uploads = 20\r\n \n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;  \u001b[41;2H Fopen wrappers ;\u001b[42;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[66X\u001b[44;2H Whether to allow the treatment of URLs (like http:// or ftp://) as files.\u001b[45;3Hhttps://php.net/allow-url-fopen\u001b[9X\r\nallow_url_fopen =\u001b[92m On\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f862,13         44\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hmost web servers.  Left undefined, PHP turns this on by default.  You can\u001b[6X\u001b[2;4Hurn it off here AT YOUR OWN RISK\u001b[3;2H **You CAN safely turn this off for IIS, in fact, you MUST.**\r\n; https://php.net/cgi.force-redirect\u001b[5;2Hcgi.force_redirect = 1\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[81X\u001b[7;4Hf cgi.nph is enabled it will force cgi to always sent Status: 200 with\u001b[8;3Hevery request. PHP's default behavior is to disable this feature.\u001b[9;2Hcgi.nph = 1\u001b[6X\r\n\u001b[37X\u001b[11;2H if cgi.force_redirect is turned on, and you are not running under Apache or Netscape\r\n; (iPlanet) web servers, you MAY need to set an environment variable name that PHP\u001b[13;3Hwill look for to know it is OK to continue execution.  Setting this variable MAY\u001b[14;3Hcause security issues, KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING FIRST.\u001b[23X\u001b[15;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.redirect-status-env\u001b[39X\u001b[16;2Hcgi.redirect_status_env =\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[40X\u001b[18;2H cgi.fix_pathinfo provides *real* PATH_INFO/PATH_TRANSLATED support for CGI.  PHP's\r\n; previous behaviour was to set PATH_TRANSLATED to SCRIPT_FILENAME, and to not grok\u001b[20;2H what PATH_INFO is.  For more information on PATH_INFO, see the cgi specs.  Setting\u001b[21;3Hthis to 1 will cause PHP CGI to fix its paths to conform to the spec.  A setting\u001b[22;2H of zero causes PHP to behave as before.  Default is 1.  You should fix your scripts\r\n; to use SCRIPT_FILENAME rather than PATH_TRANSLATED.\u001b[24;3Hhttps://php.net/cgi.fix-pathinfo   \u001b[25;2Hcgi.fix_pathinfo=1\u001b[11X\r\n\u001b[17X\n; if cgi.discard_path is enabled, the PHP CGI binary can safely be placed outside\u001b[28;3Hof the web tree and people will not be able to circumvent .htaccess security.\u001b[29;2Hcgi.discard_path=1\r\n\u001b[32X\u001b[31;2H FastCGI under IIS supports the ability to impersonate\r\n; security tokens of the calling client.  This allows IIS to define the\u001b[33;3Hsecurity context that the request runs under.  mod_fastcgi under Apache\u001b[34;3Hdoes not currently support this feature (03/17/2002)\r\n; Set to 1 if running under IIS.  Default is zero.\r\n; https://php.net/fastcgi.impersonate\u001b[37;2Hfastcgi.impersonate = 1\u001b[43X\r\n\u001b[21X\n; Prevent decoding of SCRIPT_FILENAME when using Apache ProxyPass or\u001b[40;2H ProxyPassMatch. This should be used if script file paths are not stored\u001b[41;3Hin an encoded format on the file system.\u001b[42;2H Default is 1.   \r\n;fastcgi.script_path_encoded = 0\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[45;3HDisable logging through FastCGI connection. PHP's default behavior is to enable\r\n; this feature.\u001b[5X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f18,13         42\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.248, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H\u001b[75X\u001b[2;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[10X\u001b[3;3HPaths and Directories ;\u001b[37X\u001b[4;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[11X\r\n\u001b[23X\n; UNIX: \"/path1:/path2\"\u001b[7;2Hinclude_path = \".:/php/includes\"\u001b[40X\u001b[8;2H\u001b[66X\n Windows: \"\\path1;\\path2\"\r\n;include_path = \".;c:\\php\\includes\"\u001b[11;2H\u001b[85X\u001b[12;3HPHP's default setting for include_path is \".;/path/to/php/pear\"\u001b[17X\u001b[13;3Hhttps://php.net/include-path\u001b[52X\r\n\u001b[55X\u001b[15;3HThe root of the PHP pages, used only if nonempty.\u001b[16;2H if PHP was not compiled with FORCE_REDIRECT, you SHOULD set doc_root\r\n; if you are running php as a CGI under any web server (other than IIS)\u001b[18;3Hsee documentation for security issues.  The alternate is to use the\u001b[15X\u001b[19;3Hcgi.force_redirect configuration below\u001b[43X\u001b[20;3Hhttps://php.net/doc-root\u001b[58X\r\ndoc_root =\u001b[72X\r\n\u001b[85X\u001b[23;3HThe directory under which PHP opens the script using /~username used only\u001b[24;3Hif nonempty.\u001b[20X\u001b[25;2H https://php.net/user-dir\r\nuser_dir =\r\n\u001b[81X\u001b[28;3HDirectory in which the loadable extensions (modules) reside.\u001b[17X\u001b[29;2H https://php.net/extension-dir\r\nextension_dir =\u001b[92m \"/usr/lib/php/modules/\"\u001b[31;3H\u001b[m\u000fOn windows:\u001b[42X\u001b[32;2Hextension_dir = \"ext\"\u001b[49X\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[34;3HDirectory where the temporary files should be placed.\u001b[35;3HDefaults to the system default (see sys_get_temp_dir)\u001b[36;2Hsys_temp_dir = \"/tmp\"\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[24X\n; Whether or not to enable the dl() function.  The dl() function does NOT work\u001b[39;3Hproperly in multithreaded servers, such as IIS or Zeus, and is automatically\u001b[40;3Hdisabled on them.\u001b[54X\u001b[41;3Hhttps://php.net/enable-dl\u001b[15X\r\nenable_dl =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[32X\n; cgi.force_redirect is necessary to provide security running PHP as a CGI under\u001b[45;3Hmost web servers.  Left undefined, PHP turns this on by default.  You can\u001b[6X\u001b[46;4Hurn it off here AT YOUR OWN RISK\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f774,13         39\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.246, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H; to proxy requests or to process the POST data in a memory efficient fashion.\u001b[2;2H https://php.net/enable-post-data-reading\u001b[3;2Henable_post_data_reading = Off\r\n\u001b[25X\n; Maximum size of POST data that PHP will accept.\u001b[6;3HIts value may be 0 to disable the limit. It is ignored if POST data reading\u001b[7;2H is disabled through enable_post_data_reading.\u001b[8;2H https://php.net/post-max-size\r\npost_max_size =\u001b[92m 8M\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[8X\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[11;2H Automatically add files before PHP document.\u001b[12;3Hhttps://php.net/auto-prepend-file\u001b[30X\r\nauto_prepend_file =\u001b[11X\u001b[15;3HAutomatically add files after PHP document.\u001b[6X\u001b[16;3Hhttps://php.net/auto-append-file\u001b[36X\r\nauto_append_file =\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[69X\u001b[19;3HBy default, PHP will output a media type using the Content-Type header. To\u001b[20;3Hdisable this, simply set it to be empty.\r\n;\u001b[9X\r\n; PHP's built-in default media type is set to text/html.\u001b[23;3Hhttps://php.net/default-mimetype\u001b[41X\r\ndefault_mimetype =\u001b[92m \"text/html\"\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[26X\n; PHP's default character set is set to UTF-8.\r\n; https://php.net/default-charset\r\ndefault_charset =\u001b[92m \"UTF-8\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[37X\r\n\u001b[31X\n; PHP internal character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[31;3HIf empty, default_charset is used.\u001b[32;2H https://php.net/internal-encoding\r\n;internal_encoding =\r\n\u001b[55X\u001b[35;3HPHP input character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[8X\u001b[36;2H If empty, default_charset is used.\r\n; https://php.net/input-encoding\u001b[38;2Hinput_encoding =\u001b[61X\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[40;3HPHP output character encoding is set to empty.\u001b[41;3HIf empty, default_charset is used.\r\n; See also output_buffer.\r\n; https://php.net/output-encoding\u001b[44;2Houtput_encoding =\u001b[62X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[46;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[10X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f30,13         37\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3HDevelopment Value: \"GPCS\"\u001b[51X\u001b[2;3HProduction Value: \"GPCS\";\u001b[15X\u001b[3;2H https://php.net/variables-order\r\nvariables_order =\u001b[92m \"GPCS\"\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[49X\u001b[6;3HThis directive determines which super global data (G,P & C) should be\u001b[6X\u001b[7;3Hregistered into the super global array REQUEST. If so, it also determines\u001b[8;3Hthe order in which that data is registered. The values for this directive\r\n; are specified in the same manner as the variables_order directive,\r\n; EXCEPT one. Leaving this value empty will cause PHP to use the value set\u001b[11;3Hin the variables_order directive. It does not mean it will leave the super\u001b[12;3Hglobals array REQUEST empty.\u001b[5X\r\n; Default Value: None\r\n; Development Value: \"GP\"\u001b[15;3HProduction Value: \"GP\"\u001b[21X\u001b[16;19Hrequest-order   \r\nrequest_order =\u001b[92m \"GP\"\u001b[19;3H\u001b[m\u000fThis directive determines whether PHP registers $argv & $argc each time it\u001b[20;3Hruns. $argv contains an array of all the arguments passed to PHP when a script\u001b[21;2H is invoked. $argc contains an integer representing the number of arguments\u001b[22;3Hthat were passed when the script was invoked. These arrays are extremely\u001b[23;3Huseful when running scripts from the command line. When this directive is\r\n; enabled, registering these variables consumes CPU cycles and memory each time\r\n; a script is executed. For security reasons, this feature should be disabled\u001b[26;3Hfor non-CLI SAPIs.\u001b[26X\u001b[27;3HNote: This directive is ignored for the CLI SAPI\r\n; This directive is deprecated.\r\n; https://php.net/register-argc-argv\u001b[30;2Hregister_argc_argv = Off\u001b[25X\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[32;3HWhen enabled, the ENV, REQUEST and SERVER variables are created when they're\u001b[33;2H first used (Just In Time) instead of when the script starts. If these\r\n; variables are not used within a script, having this directive on will result\u001b[35;3Hin a performance gain. The PHP directive register_argc_argv must be disabled\u001b[36;3Hfor this directive to have any effect.\u001b[37;19Hauto-globals-jit\r\nauto_globals_jit =\u001b[92m On\u001b[40;3H\u001b[m\u000fWhether PHP will read the POST data.\u001b[10X\u001b[41;3HThis option is enabled by default\u001b[42;3HMost likely, you won't want to disable this option globally. It causes $_POST\u001b[43;3Hand $_FILES to always be empty; the only way you will be able to read the\u001b[44;2H POST data will be through the php://input stream wrapper. This can be useful\r\n; to proxy requests or to process the POST data in a memory efficient fashion.\u001b[46;2H https://php.net/enable-post-data-reading\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f686,13         34\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3HAllowed values are:\u001b[6X\u001b[2;3H  ascii (all printable ASCII characters and NL)\u001b[3;3H  no-ctrl (all characters except control characters)\r\n;   all (all characters)\r\n;   raw (like \"all\", but messages are not split at newlines)\u001b[6;3Hhttps://php.net/syslog.filter\u001b[40X\u001b[7;2Hsyslog.filter = ascii\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[9;2Hwindows.show_crt_warning\u001b[43X\u001b[10;3HDefault value: 0\u001b[56X\u001b[11;3HDevelopment value: 0\u001b[54X\u001b[12;3HProduction value: 0\u001b[9X\r\n\u001b[21X\u001b[14;3HThis directive controls whether PHP will output the backtrace of fatal errors.\u001b[15;3HDefault Value: On\u001b[5X\u001b[16;3HDevelopment Value: On\u001b[8X\r\n; Production Value: On\r\n;fatal_error_backtraces = On\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[20;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[63X\u001b[21;3HData Handling ;\u001b[59X\u001b[22;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[57X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[24;3HThe separator used in PHP generated URLs to separate arguments.\u001b[14X\u001b[25;3HPHP's default setting is \"&\".\u001b[46X\u001b[26;3Hhttps://php.net/arg-separator.output\u001b[27;3HExample:\u001b[40X\u001b[28;2Harg_separator.output = \"&amp;\"\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[30;2H List of separator(s) used by PHP to parse input URLs into variables.\r\n; PHP's default setting is \"&\".\u001b[32;3HNOTE: Every character in this directive is considered as separator!\u001b[9X\u001b[33;3Hhttps://php.net/arg-separator.input\u001b[34X\u001b[34;3HExample:\u001b[68X\u001b[35;2Harg_separator.input = \";&\"\u001b[51X\r\n\u001b[40X\u001b[37;3HThis directive determines which super global arrays are registered when PHP\r\n; starts up. G,P,C,E & S are abbreviations for the following respective super\r\n; globals: GET, POST, COOKIE, ENV and SERVER. There is a performance penalty\u001b[40;3Hpaid for the registration of these arrays and because ENV is not as commonly\u001b[41;3Hused as the others, ENV is not recommended on productions servers. You\u001b[42;3Hcan still get access to the environment variables through getenv() should you\u001b[43;3Hneed to.\u001b[65X\u001b[44;3HDefault Value: \"EGPCS\"\u001b[54X\u001b[45;3HDevelopment Value: \"GPCS\"\u001b[51X\u001b[46;3HProduction Value: \"GPCS\";\u001b[15X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f42,13         32\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.030, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hand change docref_root to the base URL of your local copy including the\u001b[2;3Hleading '/'. You must also specify the file extension being used including\u001b[3;3Hthe dot. PHP's default behavior is to leave these settings empty, in which\u001b[4;3Hcase no links to documentation are generated.\u001b[5;3HNote: Never use this feature for production boxes.\u001b[8X\u001b[6;19Hdocref-root  \u001b[7;2H Examples\u001b[12X\r\n;docref_root = \"/phpmanual/\"\r\n\u001b[25X\u001b[10;3Hhttps://php.net/docref-ext\u001b[11;2Hdocref_ext = .html   \r\n\u001b[21X\n; String to output before an error message. PHP's default behavior is to leave\u001b[14;3Hthis setting blank.\u001b[59X\u001b[15;3Hhttps://php.net/error-prepend-string\u001b[16;3HExample:\u001b[13X\u001b[17;2Herror_prepend_string = \"<span style='color: #ff0000'>\"\r\n\u001b[28X\n; String to output after an error message. PHP's default behavior is to leave\u001b[20;2H this setting blank.\u001b[21;3Hhttps://php.net/error-append-string\u001b[22;2H Example:\u001b[7X\r\n;error_append_string = \"</span>\"\r\n\u001b[65X\u001b[25;3HLog errors to specified file. PHP's default behavior is to leave this value\u001b[26;3Hempty.\u001b[30X\u001b[27;3Hhttps://php.net/error-log\u001b[28;2H Example:\u001b[21X\r\n;error_log = php_errors.log\u001b[30;4Hog errors to syslog (Event Log on Windows).\u001b[24X\u001b[31;2Herror_log = syslog\u001b[12X\r\n\u001b[69X\u001b[33;3HThe syslog ident is a string which is prepended to every message logged\u001b[34;3Hto syslog. Only used when error_log is set to syslog.\u001b[35;2Hsyslog.ident = php\u001b[8X\u001b[37;5He syslog facility is used to specify what type of program is logging\u001b[5X\u001b[38;3Hthe message. Only used when error_log is set to syslog.\u001b[20X\u001b[39;2Hsyslog.facility = user\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[41;3HSet this to disable filtering control characters (the default).\u001b[7X\u001b[42;3HSome loggers only accept NVT-ASCII, others accept anything that's not\u001b[8X\u001b[43;3Hcontrol characters. If your logger accepts everything, then no filtering\u001b[44;3His needed at all.\u001b[5X\u001b[45;3HAllowed values are:\u001b[6X\u001b[46;3H  ascii (all printable ASCII characters and NL)\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f598,13         30\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[Hdisplay_startup_errors =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[3;3HBesides displaying errors, PHP can also log errors to locations such as a \u001b[4;3Hserver-specific log, STDERR, or a location specified by the error_log\u001b[5;3Hdirective found below. While errors should not be displayed on productions\u001b[6;3Hservers they should still be monitored and logging is a great way to do that.\u001b[7;3HDefault Value: Off\u001b[8;2H Development Value: On\u001b[5X\r\n; Production Value: On\u001b[10;19Hlog-errors\r\nlog_errors =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f    \u001b[13;3HDo not log repeated messages. Repeated errors must occur in same file on same\u001b[14;3Hline unless ignore_repeated_source is set true.\u001b[15;19Hignore-repeated-errors\r\nignore_repeated_errors =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[55X\n; Ignore source of message when ignoring repeated messages. When this setting\u001b[19;3His On you will not log errors with repeated messages from different files or\u001b[20;3Hsource lines.\u001b[6X\u001b[21;19Hignore-repeated-source\r\nignore_repeated_source =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[32X\n; This setting is off by default.\u001b[25;2Hreport_zend_debug = 0\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[8X\u001b[27;3HTurn off normal error reporting and emit XML-RPC error XML\u001b[28;3Hhttps://php.net/xmlrpc-errors\u001b[29;2Hxmlrpc_errors = 0\u001b[9X\r\n\u001b[46X\u001b[31;2H An XML-RPC faultCode\r\n;xmlrpc_error_number = 0\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[34;3HWhen PHP displays or logs an error, it has the capability of formatting the\u001b[35;2H error message as HTML for easier reading. This directive controls whether\r\n; the error message is formatted as HTML or not.\u001b[37;3HNote: This directive is hardcoded to Off for the CLI SAPI\u001b[13X\u001b[38;3Hhttps://php.net/html-errors\u001b[28X\u001b[39;2Hhtml_errors = On\u001b[6X\u001b[41;3HIf html_errors is set to On *and* docref_root is not empty, then PHP\u001b[42;3Hproduces clickable error messages that direct to a page describing the error\u001b[43;3Hor function causing the error in detail.\u001b[32X\u001b[44;3HYou can download a copy of the PHP manual from https://php.net/docs\u001b[45;3Hand change docref_root to the base URL of your local copy including the\u001b[46;3Hleading '/'. You must also specify the file extension being used including\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f54,13         27\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H;                     initial startup\r\n; E_COMPILE_ERROR   - fatal compile-time errors\u001b[3;3HE_COMPILE_WARNING - compile-time warnings (non-fatal errors)\u001b[13X\u001b[4;3HE_USER_ERROR      - user-generated error message\u001b[21X\u001b[5;3HE_USER_WARNING    - user-generated warning message\u001b[24X\u001b[6;3HE_USER_NOTICE     - user-generated notice message\u001b[28X\u001b[7;3HE_DEPRECATED      - warn about code that will not work in future versions\u001b[8;3H                    of PHP\u001b[9;3HE_USER_DEPRECATED - user-generated deprecation warnings\u001b[10;2H\u001b[27X\r\n; Common Values:\r\n;   E_ALL (Show all errors, warnings and notices including coding standards.)\u001b[13;3H  E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE  (Show all errors, except for notices)\u001b[19X\u001b[14;3H  E_COMPILE_ERROR|E_RECOVERABLE_ERROR|E_ERROR|E_CORE_ERROR  (Show only errors)\u001b[15;3HDefault Value: E_ALL\u001b[18X\r\n; Development Value: E_ALL  \r\n; Production Value: E_ALL & ~E_DEPRECATED\u001b[18;3Hhttps://php.net/error-reporting\u001b[44X\r\nerror_reporting =\u001b[92m E_ALL & ~E_DEPRECATED\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[39X\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[21;3HThis directive controls whether or not and where PHP will output errors,\r\n; notices and warnings too. Error output is very useful during development, but\r\n; it could be very dangerous in production environments. Depending on the code\u001b[24;3Hwhich is triggering the error, sensitive information could potentially leak\u001b[25;2H out of your application such as database usernames and passwords or worse.\r\n; For production environments, we recommend logging errors rather than\u001b[27;3Hsending them to STDOUT.\u001b[35X\u001b[28;3HPossible Values:\u001b[13X\u001b[29;2H   Off = Do not display any errors\r\n;   stderr = Display errors to STDERR (affects only CGI/CLI binaries!)\u001b[31;3H  On or stdout = Display errors to STDOUT\u001b[32;2H Default Value: On\u001b[5X\r\n; Development Value: On\u001b[34;3HProduction Value: Off\u001b[54X\u001b[35;3Hhttps://php.net/display-errors\u001b[43X\r\ndisplay_errors =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[28X\r\n\u001b[59X\u001b[38;3HThe display of errors which occur during PHP's startup sequence are handled\u001b[39;2H separately from display_errors. We strongly recommend you set this to 'off'\r\n; for production servers to avoid leaking configuration details.\u001b[41;3HDefault Value: On\u001b[51X\u001b[42;3HDevelopment Value: On\u001b[55X\u001b[43;3HProduction Value: Off\u001b[19X\u001b[44;3Hhttps://php.net/display-startup-errors\u001b[29X\r\ndisplay_startup_errors =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f10,0-1        25\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\r\u001b[A\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;2Hmax_input_vars = 1000\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[47X\u001b[3;3HHow many multipart body parts (combined input variable and file uploads) may\u001b[4;3Hbe accepted.\u001b[36X\u001b[5;3HDefault Value: -1 (Sum of max_input_vars and max_file_uploads)\u001b[6;2Hmax_multipart_body_parts = 1500\u001b[19X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[8;3HMaximum amount of memory a script may consume\u001b[9;3Hhttps://php.net/memory-limit\u001b[27X\r\nmemory_limit =\u001b[92m 128M\r\n\u001b[m\u000fmax_memory_limit =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[13;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[30X\u001b[14;3HError handling and logging ;\u001b[50X\u001b[15;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\r\n\u001b[26X\u001b[17;3HThis directive informs PHP of which errors, warnings and notices you would like\u001b[18;3Hit to take action for. The recommended way of setting values for this\r\n; directive is through the use of the error level constants and bitwise\r\n; operators. The error level constants are below here for convenience as well as\u001b[21;3Hsome common settings and their meanings.\u001b[32X\u001b[22;3HBy default, PHP is set to take action on all errors, notices and warnings EXCEPT\u001b[23;3Hthose related to E_NOTICE, which together cover best practices and\u001b[10X\u001b[24;3Hrecommended coding standards in PHP. For performance reasons, this is the  \u001b[25;3Hrecommend error reporting setting. Your production server shouldn't be wasting\u001b[26;3Hresources complaining about best practices and coding standards. That's what\u001b[27;3Hdevelopment servers and development settings are for.\u001b[28;3HNote: The php.ini-development file has this setting as E_ALL. This\u001b[29;3Hmeans it pretty much reports everything which is exactly what you want during\u001b[30;3Hdevelopment and early testing.\u001b[38X\u001b[31;2H\u001b[42X\u001b[32;3HError Level Constants:\u001b[33;3HE_ALL             - All errors and warnings\u001b[34;3HE_ERROR           - fatal run-time errors\u001b[35;3HE_RECOVERABLE_ERROR  - almost fatal run-time errors\r\n; E_WARNING         - run-time warnings (non-fatal errors)\r\n; E_PARSE           - compile-time parse errors\u001b[38;3HE_NOTICE          - run-time notices (these are warnings which often result\u001b[39;3H                    from a bug in your code, but it's possible that it was \u001b[40;3H                    intentional (e.g., using an uninitialized variable and\u001b[41;3H                    relying on the fact it is automatically initialized to an\u001b[42;3H                    empty string)\u001b[43;3HE_CORE_ERROR      - fatal errors that occur during PHP's initial startup\u001b[44;3HE_CORE_WARNING    - warnings (non-fatal errors) that occur during PHP's\r\n;                     initial startup\r\n; E_COMPILE_ERROR   - fatal compile-time errors\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f466,13         22\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;2H to a value between 0 and 1000000.\r\n; This has no effect when zend.exception_ignore_args is enabled.\u001b[3;3HDefault Value: 15\u001b[59X\u001b[4;3HDevelopment Value: 15\u001b[5;3HProduction Value: 0\u001b[43X\u001b[6;2H In production, it is recommended to set this to 0 to reduce the output\r\n; of sensitive information in stack traces.\r\nzend.exception_string_param_max_len = 0\u001b[8X\r\n\u001b[30X\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;  \r\n; Miscellaneous ;    \r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\r\n\u001b[30X\u001b[14;3HDecides whether PHP may expose the fact that it is installed on the server\u001b[15;2H (e.g. by adding its signature to the Web server header).  It is no security\r\n; threat in any way, but it makes it possible to determine whether you use PHP\u001b[17;3Hon your server or not.\u001b[57X\u001b[18;3Hhttps://php.net/expose-php\u001b[43X\r\nexpose_php =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[56X\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[21;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[23X\u001b[22;3HResource Limits ;\u001b[63X\u001b[23;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[49X\r\n\u001b[75X\u001b[25;3HMaximum execution time of each script, in seconds\u001b[29X\u001b[26;3Hhttps://php.net/max-execution-time\u001b[42X\u001b[27;3HNote: This directive is hardcoded to 0 for the CLI SAPI\r\nmax_execution_time = 30\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[79X\u001b[30;3HMaximum amount of time each script may spend parsing request data. It's a good\u001b[31;2H idea to limit this time on productions servers in order to eliminate unexpectedly\u001b[32;3Hlong running scripts. \u001b[33;3HNote: This directive is hardcoded to -1 for the CLI SAPI\u001b[34;3HDefault Value: -1 (Unlimited)\u001b[12X\u001b[35;3HDevelopment Value: 60 (60 seconds)\u001b[17X\u001b[36;3HProduction Value: 60 (60 seconds)\u001b[23X\u001b[37;3Hhttps://php.net/max-input-time\u001b[15X\r\nmax_input_time = 60\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[40;3HMaximum input variable nesting level\u001b[38X\u001b[41;3Hhttps://php.net/max-input-nesting-level\u001b[38X\u001b[42;2Hmax_input_nesting_level = 64\u001b[6X\r\n\u001b[74X\u001b[44;3HHow many GET/POST/COOKIE input variables may be accepted\u001b[15X\u001b[45;2Hmax_input_vars = 1000\u001b[15X\r\n\u001b[47X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f22,0-1        20\r\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\r\u001b[A\u001b[A\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H\u001b[35X\u001b[2;3HIf enabled, the request will be allowed to complete even if the user aborts\u001b[3;3Hthe request. Consider enabling it if executing long requests, which may end up\u001b[4;3Hbeing interrupted by the user or a browser timing out. PHP's default behavior\u001b[5;3His to disable this feature.\u001b[6;3Hhttps://php.net/ignore-user-abort\u001b[37X\u001b[7;2Hignore_user_abort = On\u001b[20X\r\n\u001b[39X\n; Determines the size of the realpath cache to be used by PHP. This value should\u001b[10;2H be increased on systems where PHP opens many files to reflect the quantity of\u001b[11;3Hthe file operations performed.\u001b[12;2H Note: if open_basedir is set, the cache is disabled\r\n; https://php.net/realpath-cache-size\u001b[14;2Hrealpath_cache_size = 4096k\u001b[48X\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[16;3HDuration of time, in seconds for which to cache realpath information for a given\u001b[17;3Hfile or directory. For systems with rarely changing files, consider increasing this\u001b[18;3Hvalue.\u001b[20X\r\n; https://php.net/realpath-cache-ttl\r\n;realpath_cache_ttl = 120\r\n\u001b[19X\u001b[22;3HEnables or disables the circular reference collector.\u001b[23;2H https://php.net/zend.enable-gc\r\nzend.enable_gc =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[51X\u001b[26;3HIf enabled, scripts may be written in encodings that are incompatible with\u001b[27;3Hthe scanner.  CP936, Big5, CP949 and Shift_JIS are the examples of such\r\n; encodings.  To use this feature, mbstring extension must be enabled.\r\n;zend.multibyte = Off\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[31;3HAllows to set the default encoding for the scripts.  This value will be used\u001b[5X\u001b[32;3Hunless \"declare(encoding=...)\" directive appears at the top of the script.\u001b[33;3HOnly affects if zend.multibyte is set.\u001b[18X\u001b[34;2Hzend.script_encoding =\u001b[8X\r\n\u001b[36X\u001b[36;3HAllows to include or exclude arguments from stack traces generated for exceptions.\u001b[37;3HIn production, it is recommended to turn this setting on to prohibit the output\r\n; of sensitive information in stack traces\r\n; Default Value: Off\u001b[40;3HDevelopment Value: Off\u001b[14X\u001b[41;3HProduction Value: On\u001b[19X\r\nzend.exception_ignore_args =\u001b[92m On\u001b[44;3H\u001b[m\u000fAllows setting the maximum string length in an argument of a stringified stack trace\u001b[45;2H to a value between 0 and 1000000.\r\n; This has no effect when zend.exception_ignore_args is enabled.\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f378,13         18\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[2;3HThe unserialize callback function will be called (with the undefined class'\u001b[3;3Hname as parameter), if the unserializer finds an undefined class\u001b[14X\u001b[4;3Hwhich should be instantiated. A warning appears if the specified function is \u001b[5;3Hnot defined, or if the function doesn't include/implement the missing class.\u001b[6;3HSo only set this entry, if you really want to implement such a\u001b[7;2H callback-function.   \r\nunserialize_callback_func =\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[10;3HThe unserialize_max_depth specifies the default depth limit for unserialized \u001b[11;3Hstructures. Setting the depth limit too high may result in stack overflows\u001b[12;3Hduring unserialization. The unserialize_max_depth ini setting can be\u001b[13;3Hoverridden by the max_depth option on individual unserialize() calls.\u001b[14;2H A value of 0 disables the depth limit.\r\n;unserialize_max_depth = 4096\r\n\u001b[82X\u001b[17;3HWhen floats & doubles are serialized, store serialize_precision significant\u001b[8X\u001b[18;3Hdigits after the floating point. The default value ensures that when floats\u001b[19;3Hare decoded with unserialize, the data will remain the same.\u001b[20;2H The value is also used for json_encode when encoding double values.\r\n; If -1 is used, then dtoa mode 0 is used which automatically select the best\u001b[22;3Hprecision.\u001b[43X\r\nserialize_precision =\u001b[92m -1\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[8X\r\n\u001b[19X\n; open_basedir, if set, limits all file operations to the defined directory\u001b[26;3Hand below.  This directive makes most sense if used in a per-directory    \u001b[27;3Hor per-virtualhost web server configuration file.\u001b[22X\u001b[28;3HNote: disables the realpath cache\u001b[35X\u001b[29;2H https://php.net/open-basedir\r\n;open_basedir =\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[32;3HThis directive allows you to disable certain functions.\u001b[19X\u001b[33;3HIt receives a comma-delimited list of function names.\u001b[34;2H https://php.net/disable-functions\r\ndisable_functions =\r\n\u001b[84X\u001b[37;3HColors for Syntax Highlighting mode.  Anything that's acceptable in\u001b[12X\u001b[38;3H<span style=\"color: ???????\"> would work.\u001b[39;3Hhttps://php.net/syntax-highlighting\u001b[40;2Hhighlight.string  = #DD0000\u001b[41;2Hhighlight.comment = #FF9900\r\n;highlight.keyword = #007700   \r\n;highlight.default = #0000BB\u001b[44;2Hhighlight.html    = #000000\u001b[58X\r\n\u001b[35X\u001b[46;3HIf enabled, the request will be allowed to complete even if the user aborts\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f34,13         15\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[H; \"form\" tag is special tag. It will add hidden input tag to pass values.\u001b[2;3HRefer to session.trans_sid_tags for usage.\u001b[33X\u001b[3;3HDefault Value: \"form=\"\u001b[42X\u001b[4;3HDevelopment Value: \"form=\"\u001b[50X\u001b[5;3HProduction Value: \"form=\"\u001b[51X\u001b[6;2Hurl_rewriter.tags\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[20X\n; URL rewriter will not rewrite absolute URL nor form by default. To enable\r\n; absolute URL rewrite, allowed hosts must be defined at RUNTIME.\u001b[10;3HRefer to session.trans_sid_hosts for more details.\u001b[26X\u001b[11;3HDefault Value: \"\"\u001b[57X\u001b[12;3HDevelopment Value: \"\"\u001b[47X\u001b[13;3HProduction Value: \"\"\u001b[49X\u001b[14;2Hurl_rewriter.hosts\u001b[21X\r\n\u001b[29X\n; Transparent output compression using the zlib library\u001b[17;3HValid values for this option are 'off', 'on', or a specific buffer size    \u001b[18;3Hto be used for compression (default is 4KB)\u001b[32X\u001b[19;3HNote: Resulting chunk size may vary due to nature of compression. PHP\u001b[20;3H  outputs chunks that are few hundreds bytes each as a result of   \u001b[21;3H  compression. If you prefer a larger chunk size for better\u001b[16X\u001b[22;3H  performance, enable output_buffering in addition.\r\n; Note: You need to use zlib.output_handler instead of the standard\r\n;   output_handler, or otherwise the output will be corrupted.\u001b[25;3Hhttps://php.net/zlib.output-compression\u001b[34X\r\nzlib.output_compression =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[43X\r\n\u001b[51X\u001b[28;3Hhttps://php.net/zlib.output-compression-level\u001b[29;2Hzlib.output_compression_level = -1\r\n\u001b[15X\n; You cannot specify additional output handlers if zlib.output_compression\u001b[32;3His activated here. This setting does the same as output_handler but in\u001b[33;3Ha different order.\u001b[35X\u001b[34;19Hzlib.output-handler\r\n;zlib.output_handler =\u001b[37;3HImplicit flush tells PHP to tell the output layer to flush itself  \u001b[38;3Hautomatically after every output block.  This is equivalent to calling the\u001b[39;3HPHP function flush() after each and every call to print() or echo() and each\u001b[40;2H and every HTML block.  Turning this option on has serious performance\u001b[41;2H implications and is generally recommended for debugging purposes only.\u001b[42;2H https://php.net/implicit-flush\u001b[43;2H Note: This directive is hardcoded to On for the CLI SAPI\r\nimplicit_flush =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[8X\u001b[46;3HThe unserialize callback function will be called (with the undefined class'\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f290,13         13\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hhttps://php.net/precision\u001b[46X\r\nprecision = 14\u001b[30X\r\n\u001b[24X\u001b[4;3HOutput buffering is a mechanism for controlling how much output data\u001b[5;3H(excluding headers and cookies) PHP should keep internally before pushing that\u001b[6;2H data to the client. If your application's output exceeds this setting, PHP\r\n; will send that data in chunks of roughly the size you specify.\u001b[8;3HTurning on this setting and managing its maximum buffer size can yield some\u001b[9;3Hinteresting side-effects depending on your application and web server.\u001b[10;3HYou may be able to send headers and cookies after you've already sent output\u001b[11;3Hthrough print or echo. You also may see performance benefits if your server is\u001b[12;3Hemitting less packets due to buffered output versus PHP streaming the output\u001b[13;3Has it gets it. On production servers, 4096 bytes is a good setting for performance\u001b[14;2H reasons.\u001b[9X\r\n; Note: Output buffering can also be controlled via Output Buffering Control\u001b[16;3H  functions.\u001b[41X\u001b[17;3HPossible Values:\u001b[55X\u001b[18;3H  On = Enabled and buffer is unlimited. (Use with caution)\u001b[19;3H  Off = Disabled\u001b[53X\u001b[20;5HInteger = Enables the buffer and sets its maximum size in bytes.\u001b[21;3HNote: This directive is hardcoded to Off for the CLI SAPI  \u001b[22;3HDefault Value: Off\u001b[33X\u001b[23;3HDevelopment Value: 4096\u001b[42X\u001b[24;3HProduction Value: 4096\u001b[38X\u001b[25;19Houtput-buffering\u001b[7X\r\noutput_buffering = 4096\u001b[6X\u001b[28;3HYou can redirect all of the output of your scripts to a function.  For\u001b[29;2H example, if you set output_handler to \"mb_output_handler\", character\r\n; encoding will be transparently converted to the specified encoding.\u001b[31;3HSetting any output handler automatically turns on output buffering.\u001b[5X\u001b[32;3HNote: People who wrote portable scripts should not depend on this ini \u001b[33;3H  directive. Instead, explicitly set the output handler using ob_start().\u001b[34;3H  Using this ini directive may cause problems unless you know what script\u001b[35;2H   is doing.\u001b[9X\r\n; Note: You cannot use both \"mb_output_handler\" with \"ob_iconv_handler\"\u001b[37;3H  and you cannot use both \"ob_gzhandler\" and \"zlib.output_compression\".\u001b[38;3HNote: output_handler must be empty if this is set 'On' !!!!\u001b[15X\u001b[39;3H  Instead you must use zlib.output_handler.\u001b[33X\u001b[40;3Hhttps://php.net/output-handler\u001b[39X\u001b[41;2Houtput_handler =\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[32X\u001b[43;3HURL rewriter function rewrites URL on the fly by using  \r\n; output buffer. You can set target tags by this configuration.\r\n; \"form\" tag is special tag. It will add hidden input tag to pass values.\u001b[46;3HRefer to session.trans_sid_tags for usage.\u001b[33X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f46,13         10\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3Hzend.exception_ignore_args\r\n;   Default Value: Off\r\n;   Development Value: Off\u001b[4;3H  Production Value: On\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[6;3Hzend.exception_string_param_max_len\u001b[39X\u001b[7;3H  Default Value: 15\u001b[43X\u001b[8;3H  Development Value: 15\u001b[52X\u001b[9;3H  Production Value: 0\u001b[49X\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[11;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[60X\u001b[12;3Hphp.ini Options  ;\u001b[58X\u001b[13;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[64X\u001b[14;3HName for user-defined php.ini (.htaccess) files. Default is \".user.ini\"\u001b[15;2Huser_ini.filename = \".user.ini\"\u001b[44X\r\n\u001b[14X\u001b[17;3HTo disable this feature set this option to an empty value\u001b[18;2Huser_ini.filename =\u001b[40X\r\n\u001b[18X\u001b[20;3HTTL for user-defined php.ini files (time-to-live) in seconds. Default is 300 seconds (5 minutes)\u001b[21;2Huser_ini.cache_ttl = 300\u001b[34X\r\n\u001b[20X\u001b[23;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[5X\u001b[24;3HLanguage Options ;    \u001b[25;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[14X\r\n\u001b[23X\n; Enable the PHP scripting language engine under Apache.\u001b[28;3Hhttps://php.net/engine\u001b[48X\r\nengine =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[59X\r\n\u001b[69X\u001b[31;3HThis directive determines whether or not PHP will recognize code between\u001b[32;3H<? and ?> tags as PHP source which should be processed as such. It is\u001b[33;3Hgenerally recommended that <?php and ?> should be used and that this feature\u001b[34;3Hshould be disabled, as enabling it may result in issues when generating XML\u001b[35;3Hdocuments, however this remains supported for backward compatibility reasons.\u001b[36;7H that this directive does not control the <?= shorthand tag, which can be\u001b[37;3Hused regardless of this directive.\u001b[37X\u001b[38;3HDefault Value: On\u001b[42X\u001b[39;3HDevelopment Value: Off\u001b[21X\u001b[40;3HProduction Value: Off\u001b[9X\u001b[41;2H https://php.net/short-open-tag\r\nshort_open_tag =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[56X\u001b[44;3HThe number of significant digits displayed in floating point numbers.\u001b[45;3Hhttps://php.net/precision\u001b[46X\r\nprecision = 14\u001b[30X\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f02,13          8\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.030, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;3H  Default Value: Off\u001b[6X\u001b[2;7Hvelopment Value: On\u001b[3;5HProduction Value: On  \r\n\u001b[24X\n; max_input_time\u001b[6;3H  Default Value: -1 (Unlimited)    \u001b[7;7Hvelopment Value: 60 (60 seconds)\u001b[8;5HProduction Value: 60 (60 seconds)\r\n\u001b[23X\n; mysqlnd.collect_memory_statistics\u001b[11;2H   Default Value: Off\u001b[12;3H  Development Value: On\u001b[13;2H   Production Value: Off\r\n\u001b[73X\u001b[15;2H output_buffering\u001b[14X\r\n;   Default Value: Off\u001b[17;3H  Development Value: 4096\u001b[32X\u001b[18;2H   Production Value: 4096\u001b[20;3Hrequest_order\u001b[83X\u001b[21;2H   Default Value: None  \r\n;   Development Value: \"GP\"\u001b[23;2H   Production Value: \"GP\"\r\n\u001b[20X\u001b[25;2H session.gc_divisor\r\n;   Default Value: 100\u001b[27;3H  Development Value: 1000\u001b[29X\u001b[28;3H  Production Value: 1000\r\n\u001b[11X\n; short_open_tag\u001b[31;3H  Default Value: On\u001b[53X\u001b[32;3H  Development Value: Off\u001b[45X\u001b[33;3H  Production Value: Off\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[35;3Hvariables_order\u001b[62X\u001b[36;3H  Default Value: \"EGPCS\"\u001b[53X\u001b[37;3H  Development Value: \"GPCS\"\u001b[7X\u001b[38;3H  Production Value: \"GPCS\"\r\n\u001b[24X\u001b[40;3Hzend.assertions\u001b[6X\u001b[41;3H  Default Value: 1\u001b[12X\r\n;   Development Value: 1\r\n;   Production Value: -1\r\n\u001b[71X\u001b[45;3Hzend.exception_ignore_args\r\n;   Default Value: Off\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f158,13          6\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.029, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;   \u001b[2;3HAbout this file ;\u001b[6X\u001b[3;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[5X\r\n; PHP comes packaged with two INI files. One that is recommended to be used\u001b[5;3Hin production environments and one that is recommended to be used in\u001b[6;3Hdevelopment environments.\u001b[6X\r\n\u001b[38X\u001b[8;3Hphp.ini-production contains settings which hold security, performance and\r\n; best practices at its core. But please be aware, these settings may break\u001b[10;3Hcompatibility with older or less security-conscious applications. We\u001b[11;3Hrecommending using the production ini in production and testing environments.\r\n\u001b[25X\u001b[13;3Hphp.ini-development is very similar to its production variant, except it is\r\n; much more verbose when it comes to errors. We recommend using the\u001b[15;3Hdevelopment version only in development environments, as errors shown to\u001b[16;3Happlication users can inadvertently leak otherwise secure information.\r\n\u001b[27X\u001b[18;3HThis is the php.ini-production INI file.\u001b[20;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[21;3HQuick Reference ;    \u001b[22;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[8X\r\n\u001b[26X\n; The following are all the settings which are different in either the production\u001b[25;3Hor development versions of the INIs with respect to PHP's default behavior.\u001b[26;3HPlease see the actual settings later in the document for more details as to why\u001b[27;3Hwe recommend these changes in PHP's behavior.\r\n\u001b[26X\n; display_errors\u001b[30;3H  Default Value: On\u001b[31;7Hvelopment Value: On\u001b[32;5HProduction Value: Off \r\n\u001b[25X\n; display_startup_errors\u001b[35;3H  Default Value: On\u001b[36;7Hvelopment Value: On \u001b[37;5HProduction Value: Off    \r\n\u001b[28X\n; error_reporting\u001b[40;3H  Default Value: E_ALL\u001b[41;7Hvelopment Value: E_ALL\u001b[42;5HProduction Value: E_ALL & ~E_DEPRECATED\r\n\u001b[24X\n; log_errors\u001b[45;3H  Default Value: Off\u001b[6X\u001b[46;7Hvelopment Value: On\u001b[47;154H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f14,13          3\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.031, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;2H they might mean something in the future.\r\n\u001b[19X\u001b[3;2H Directives following the section heading [PATH=/www/mysite] only\u001b[4;3Happly to PHP files in the /www/mysite directory.  Directives\u001b[13X\u001b[5;3Hfollowing the section heading [HOST=www.example.com] only apply to  \u001b[6;3HPHP files served from www.example.com.  Directives set in these\r\n; special sections cannot be overridden by user-defined INI files or\u001b[8;3Hat runtime. Currently, [PATH=] and [HOST=] sections only work under\u001b[6X\u001b[9;3HCGI/FastCGI.\u001b[61X\u001b[10;3Hhttps://php.net/ini.sections\u001b[40X\r\n\u001b[79X\n; Directives are specified using the following syntax:\u001b[13;3Hdirective = value\u001b[58X\u001b[14;3HDirective names are *case sensitive* - foo=bar is different from FOO=bar.\u001b[15;3HDirectives are variables used to configure PHP or PHP extensions.\u001b[7X\u001b[16;3HThere is no name validation.  If PHP can't find an expected\u001b[11X\r\n; directive because it is not set or is mistyped, a default value will be used.\r\n\u001b[42X\n; The value can be a string, a number, a PHP constant (e.g. E_ALL or M_PI), one\u001b[20;2H of the INI constants (On, Off, True, False, Yes, No and None) or an expression\u001b[21;3H(e.g. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted string (\"bar\"), or a reference to a\u001b[22;2H previously set variable or directive (e.g. ${foo})\u001b[24;3HExpressions in the INI file are limited to bitwise operators and parentheses:  \u001b[25;3H|  bitwise OR\u001b[62X\u001b[26;3H^  bitwise XOR\u001b[65X\u001b[27;3H&  bitwise AND\u001b[31X\r\n; ~  bitwise NOT\u001b[29;3H!  boolean NOT\r\n\u001b[21X\u001b[31;3HBoolean flags can be turned on using the values 1, On, True or Yes.\u001b[32;3HThey can be turned off using the values 0, Off, False or No.\u001b[34;3HAn empty string can be denoted by simply not writing anything after the equal\u001b[35;3Hsign, or by using the None keyword:\r\n\u001b[25X\u001b[37;3Hfoo =         ; sets foo to an empty string\r\n; foo = None    ; sets foo to an empty string\u001b[39;3Hfoo = \"None\"  ; sets foo to the string 'None'\r\n\u001b[24X\u001b[41;3HIf you use constants in your value, and these constants belong to a\u001b[42;3Hdynamically loaded extension (either a PHP extension or a Zend extension),\r\n; you may only use these constants *after* the line that loads the extension.\r\n\u001b[12X\u001b[45;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;   \u001b[46;3HAbout this file ;\u001b[6X\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f70,13           1\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.028, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.003, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[1;46r\u001b[H\u001b[24L\u001b[1;48r\u001b[H\u001b[96m[PHP]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; About php.ini   ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; PHP's initialization file, generally called php.ini, is responsible for\u001b[K\r\n; configuring many of the aspects of PHP's behavior.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; PHP attempts to find and load this configuration from a number of locations.\u001b[K\r\n; The following is a summary of its search order:\u001b[K\r\n; 1. SAPI module specific location.\u001b[K\r\n; 2. The PHPRC environment variable.\u001b[K\r\n; 3. A number of predefined registry keys on Windows\u001b[K\r\n; 4. Current working directory (except CLI)\u001b[K\r\n; 5. The web server's directory (for SAPI modules), or directory of PHP\u001b[K\r\n; (otherwise in Windows)\u001b[K\r\n; 6. The directory from the --with-config-file-path compile time option, or the\u001b[K\r\n; Windows directory (usually C:\\windows)\u001b[K\r\n; See the PHP docs for more specific information.\u001b[K\r\n; https://php.net/configuration.file\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; The syntax of the file is extremely simple.  Whitespace and lines\u001b[K\r\n; beginning with a semicolon are silently ignored (as you probably guessed).\u001b[K\r\n; Section headers (e.g. [Foo]) are also silently ignored, even though\u001b[K\u001b[47;153H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f46,13          Top\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.031, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H\u001b[m\u000f~@k\u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?25l\u001b[48;160H   \u001b[46;13H\u001b[?25h"]
